8//
9// This file implements routines for folding instructions into simpler forms
10// that do not require creating new instructions. This does constant folding
11// ("add i32 1, 1" -> "2") but can also handle non-constant operands, either
12// returning a constant ("and i32 %x, 0" -> "0") or an already existing value
13// ("and i32 %x, %x" -> "%x"). All operands are assumed to have already been
14// simplified: This is usually true and assuming it simplifies the logic (if
15// they have not been simplified then results are correct but maybe suboptimal).
16//
17//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

73static Value *foldSelectWithBinaryOp(Value *Cond, Value *TrueVal,
74 Value *FalseVal) {
75 BinaryOperator::BinaryOps BinOpCode;
76 if (auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Cond))
77 BinOpCode = BO->getOpcode();
78 else
79 return nullptr;
80
81 CmpInst::Predicate ExpectedPred, Pred1, Pred2;
82 if (BinOpCode == BinaryOperator::Or) {
83 ExpectedPred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
84 } else if (BinOpCode == BinaryOperator::And) {
85 ExpectedPred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
86 } else
87 return nullptr;
88
89 // %A = icmp eq %TV, %FV
90 // %B = icmp eq %X, %Y (and one of these is a select operand)
91 // %C = and %A, %B
92 // %D = select %C, %TV, %FV
93 // -->
94 // %FV
95
96 // %A = icmp ne %TV, %FV
97 // %B = icmp ne %X, %Y (and one of these is a select operand)
98 // %C = or %A, %B
99 // %D = select %C, %TV, %FV
100 // -->
101 // %TV
102 Value *X, *Y;
103 if (!match(Cond, m_c_BinOp(m_c_ICmp(Pred1, m_Specific(TrueVal),
104 m_Specific(FalseVal)),
105 m_ICmp(Pred2, m_Value(X), m_Value(Y)))) ||
106 Pred1 != Pred2 || Pred1 != ExpectedPred)
107 return nullptr;
108
109 if (X == TrueVal || X == FalseVal || Y == TrueVal || Y == FalseVal)
110 return BinOpCode == BinaryOperator::Or ? TrueVal : FalseVal;
111
112 return nullptr;
113}

115/// For a boolean type or a vector of boolean type, return false or a vector
116/// with every element false.
117static Constant *getFalse(Type *Ty) {
118 return ConstantInt::getFalse(Ty);
119}
120
121/// For a boolean type or a vector of boolean type, return true or a vector
122/// with every element true.
123static Constant *getTrue(Type *Ty) {
124 return ConstantInt::getTrue(Ty);
125}

127/// isSameCompare - Is V equivalent to the comparison "LHS Pred RHS"?
128static bool isSameCompare(Value *V, CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
129 Value *RHS) {
130 CmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(V);
131 if (!Cmp)
132 return false;
133 CmpInst::Predicate CPred = Cmp->getPredicate();
134 Value *CLHS = Cmp->getOperand(0), *CRHS = Cmp->getOperand(1);
135 if (CPred == Pred && CLHS == LHS && CRHS == RHS)
136 return true;
137 return CPred == CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred) && CLHS == RHS &&
138 CRHS == LHS;
139}

141/// Does the given value dominate the specified phi node?
142static bool valueDominatesPHI(Value *V, PHINode *P, const DominatorTree *DT) {
143 Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
144 if (!I)
145 // Arguments and constants dominate all instructions.
146 return true;
147
148 // If we are processing instructions (and/or basic blocks) that have not been
149 // fully added to a function, the parent nodes may still be null. Simply
150 // return the conservative answer in these cases.
151 if (!I->getParent() || !P->getParent() || !I->getFunction())
152 return false;
153
154 // If we have a DominatorTree then do a precise test.
155 if (DT)
156 return DT->dominates(I, P);
157
158 // Otherwise, if the instruction is in the entry block and is not an invoke,
159 // then it obviously dominates all phi nodes.
160 if (I->getParent() == &I->getFunction()->getEntryBlock() &&
161 !isa<InvokeInst>(I))
162 return true;
163
164 return false;
165}

167/// Simplify "A op (B op' C)" by distributing op over op', turning it into
168/// "(A op B) op' (A op C)". Here "op" is given by Opcode and "op'" is
169/// given by OpcodeToExpand, while "A" corresponds to LHS and "B op' C" to RHS.
170/// Also performs the transform "(A op' B) op C" -> "(A op C) op' (B op C)".
171/// Returns the simplified value, or null if no simplification was performed.
172static Value *ExpandBinOp(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
173 Instruction::BinaryOps OpcodeToExpand,
174 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
175 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
176 if (!MaxRecurse--)
177 return nullptr;
178
179 // Check whether the expression has the form "(A op' B) op C".
180 if (BinaryOperator *Op0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(LHS))
181 if (Op0->getOpcode() == OpcodeToExpand) {
182 // It does! Try turning it into "(A op C) op' (B op C)".
183 Value *A = Op0->getOperand(0), *B = Op0->getOperand(1), *C = RHS;
184 // Do "A op C" and "B op C" both simplify?
185 if (Value *L = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, A, C, Q, MaxRecurse))
186 if (Value *R = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, B, C, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
187 // They do! Return "L op' R" if it simplifies or is already available.
188 // If "L op' R" equals "A op' B" then "L op' R" is just the LHS.
189 if ((L == A && R == B) || (Instruction::isCommutative(OpcodeToExpand)
190 && L == B && R == A)) {
191 ++NumExpand;
192 return LHS;
193 }
194 // Otherwise return "L op' R" if it simplifies.
195 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(OpcodeToExpand, L, R, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
196 ++NumExpand;
197 return V;
198 }
199 }
200 }
201
202 // Check whether the expression has the form "A op (B op' C)".
203 if (BinaryOperator *Op1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(RHS))
204 if (Op1->getOpcode() == OpcodeToExpand) {
205 // It does! Try turning it into "(A op B) op' (A op C)".
206 Value *A = LHS, *B = Op1->getOperand(0), *C = Op1->getOperand(1);
207 // Do "A op B" and "A op C" both simplify?
208 if (Value *L = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, A, B, Q, MaxRecurse))
209 if (Value *R = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, A, C, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
210 // They do! Return "L op' R" if it simplifies or is already available.
211 // If "L op' R" equals "B op' C" then "L op' R" is just the RHS.
212 if ((L == B && R == C) || (Instruction::isCommutative(OpcodeToExpand)
213 && L == C && R == B)) {
214 ++NumExpand;
215 return RHS;
216 }
217 // Otherwise return "L op' R" if it simplifies.
218 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(OpcodeToExpand, L, R, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
219 ++NumExpand;
220 return V;
221 }
222 }
223 }
224
225 return nullptr;
226}

228/// Generic simplifications for associative binary operations.
229/// Returns the simpler value, or null if none was found.
230static Value *SimplifyAssociativeBinOp(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode,
231 Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
232 const SimplifyQuery &Q,
233 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
234 assert(Instruction::isAssociative(Opcode) && "Not an associative operation!");
235
236 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
237 if (!MaxRecurse--)
238 return nullptr;
239
240 BinaryOperator *Op0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(LHS);
241 BinaryOperator *Op1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(RHS);
242
243 // Transform: "(A op B) op C" ==> "A op (B op C)" if it simplifies completely.
244 if (Op0 && Op0->getOpcode() == Opcode) {
245 Value *A = Op0->getOperand(0);
246 Value *B = Op0->getOperand(1);
247 Value *C = RHS;
248
249 // Does "B op C" simplify?
250 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, B, C, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
251 // It does! Return "A op V" if it simplifies or is already available.
252 // If V equals B then "A op V" is just the LHS.
253 if (V == B) return LHS;
254 // Otherwise return "A op V" if it simplifies.
255 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, A, V, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
256 ++NumReassoc;
257 return W;
258 }
259 }
260 }
261
262 // Transform: "A op (B op C)" ==> "(A op B) op C" if it simplifies completely.
263 if (Op1 && Op1->getOpcode() == Opcode) {
264 Value *A = LHS;
265 Value *B = Op1->getOperand(0);
266 Value *C = Op1->getOperand(1);
267
268 // Does "A op B" simplify?
269 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, A, B, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
270 // It does! Return "V op C" if it simplifies or is already available.
271 // If V equals B then "V op C" is just the RHS.
272 if (V == B) return RHS;
273 // Otherwise return "V op C" if it simplifies.
274 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, V, C, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
275 ++NumReassoc;
276 return W;
277 }
278 }
279 }
280
281 // The remaining transforms require commutativity as well as associativity.
282 if (!Instruction::isCommutative(Opcode))
283 return nullptr;
284
285 // Transform: "(A op B) op C" ==> "(C op A) op B" if it simplifies completely.
286 if (Op0 && Op0->getOpcode() == Opcode) {
287 Value *A = Op0->getOperand(0);
288 Value *B = Op0->getOperand(1);
289 Value *C = RHS;
290
291 // Does "C op A" simplify?
292 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, C, A, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
293 // It does! Return "V op B" if it simplifies or is already available.
294 // If V equals A then "V op B" is just the LHS.
295 if (V == A) return LHS;
296 // Otherwise return "V op B" if it simplifies.
297 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, V, B, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
298 ++NumReassoc;
299 return W;
300 }
301 }
302 }
303
304 // Transform: "A op (B op C)" ==> "B op (C op A)" if it simplifies completely.
305 if (Op1 && Op1->getOpcode() == Opcode) {
306 Value *A = LHS;
307 Value *B = Op1->getOperand(0);
308 Value *C = Op1->getOperand(1);
309
310 // Does "C op A" simplify?
311 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, C, A, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
312 // It does! Return "B op V" if it simplifies or is already available.
313 // If V equals C then "B op V" is just the RHS.
314 if (V == C) return RHS;
315 // Otherwise return "B op V" if it simplifies.
316 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, B, V, Q, MaxRecurse)) {
317 ++NumReassoc;
318 return W;
319 }
320 }
321 }
322
323 return nullptr;
324}

326/// In the case of a binary operation with a select instruction as an operand,
327/// try to simplify the binop by seeing whether evaluating it on both branches
328/// of the select results in the same value. Returns the common value if so,
329/// otherwise returns null.
330static Value *ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *LHS,
331 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
332 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
333 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
334 if (!MaxRecurse--)
335 return nullptr;
336
337 SelectInst *SI;
338 if (isa<SelectInst>(LHS)) {
339 SI = cast<SelectInst>(LHS);
340 } else {
341 assert(isa<SelectInst>(RHS) && "No select instruction operand!");
342 SI = cast<SelectInst>(RHS);
343 }
344
345 // Evaluate the BinOp on the true and false branches of the select.
346 Value *TV;
347 Value *FV;
348 if (SI == LHS) {
349 TV = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, SI->getTrueValue(), RHS, Q, MaxRecurse);
350 FV = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, SI->getFalseValue(), RHS, Q, MaxRecurse);
351 } else {
352 TV = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, LHS, SI->getTrueValue(), Q, MaxRecurse);
353 FV = SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, LHS, SI->getFalseValue(), Q, MaxRecurse);
354 }
355
356 // If they simplified to the same value, then return the common value.
357 // If they both failed to simplify then return null.
358 if (TV == FV)
359 return TV;
360
361 // If one branch simplified to undef, return the other one.
362 if (TV && isa<UndefValue>(TV))
363 return FV;
364 if (FV && isa<UndefValue>(FV))
365 return TV;
366
367 // If applying the operation did not change the true and false select values,
368 // then the result of the binop is the select itself.
369 if (TV == SI->getTrueValue() && FV == SI->getFalseValue())
370 return SI;
371
372 // If one branch simplified and the other did not, and the simplified
373 // value is equal to the unsimplified one, return the simplified value.
374 // For example, select (cond, X, X & Z) & Z -> X & Z.
375 if ((FV && !TV) || (TV && !FV)) {
376 // Check that the simplified value has the form "X op Y" where "op" is the
377 // same as the original operation.
378 Instruction *Simplified = dyn_cast<Instruction>(FV ? FV : TV);
379 if (Simplified && Simplified->getOpcode() == unsigned(Opcode)) {
380 // The value that didn't simplify is "UnsimplifiedLHS op UnsimplifiedRHS".
381 // We already know that "op" is the same as for the simplified value. See
382 // if the operands match too. If so, return the simplified value.
383 Value *UnsimplifiedBranch = FV ? SI->getTrueValue() : SI->getFalseValue();
384 Value *UnsimplifiedLHS = SI == LHS ? UnsimplifiedBranch : LHS;
385 Value *UnsimplifiedRHS = SI == LHS ? RHS : UnsimplifiedBranch;
386 if (Simplified->getOperand(0) == UnsimplifiedLHS &&
387 Simplified->getOperand(1) == UnsimplifiedRHS)
388 return Simplified;
389 if (Simplified->isCommutative() &&
390 Simplified->getOperand(1) == UnsimplifiedLHS &&
391 Simplified->getOperand(0) == UnsimplifiedRHS)
392 return Simplified;
393 }
394 }
395
396 return nullptr;
397}

399/// In the case of a comparison with a select instruction, try to simplify the
400/// comparison by seeing whether both branches of the select result in the same
401/// value. Returns the common value if so, otherwise returns null.
402static Value *ThreadCmpOverSelect(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
403 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
404 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
405 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
406 if (!MaxRecurse--)
407 return nullptr;
408
409 // Make sure the select is on the LHS.
410 if (!isa<SelectInst>(LHS)) {
411 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
412 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
413 }
414 assert(isa<SelectInst>(LHS) && "Not comparing with a select instruction!");
415 SelectInst *SI = cast<SelectInst>(LHS);
416 Value *Cond = SI->getCondition();
417 Value *TV = SI->getTrueValue();
418 Value *FV = SI->getFalseValue();
419
420 // Now that we have "cmp select(Cond, TV, FV), RHS", analyse it.
421 // Does "cmp TV, RHS" simplify?
422 Value *TCmp = SimplifyCmpInst(Pred, TV, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse);
423 if (TCmp == Cond) {
424 // It not only simplified, it simplified to the select condition. Replace
425 // it with 'true'.
426 TCmp = getTrue(Cond->getType());
427 } else if (!TCmp) {
428 // It didn't simplify. However if "cmp TV, RHS" is equal to the select
429 // condition then we can replace it with 'true'. Otherwise give up.
430 if (!isSameCompare(Cond, Pred, TV, RHS))
431 return nullptr;
432 TCmp = getTrue(Cond->getType());
433 }
434
435 // Does "cmp FV, RHS" simplify?
436 Value *FCmp = SimplifyCmpInst(Pred, FV, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse);
437 if (FCmp == Cond) {
438 // It not only simplified, it simplified to the select condition. Replace
439 // it with 'false'.
440 FCmp = getFalse(Cond->getType());
441 } else if (!FCmp) {
442 // It didn't simplify. However if "cmp FV, RHS" is equal to the select
443 // condition then we can replace it with 'false'. Otherwise give up.
444 if (!isSameCompare(Cond, Pred, FV, RHS))
445 return nullptr;
446 FCmp = getFalse(Cond->getType());
447 }
448
449 // If both sides simplified to the same value, then use it as the result of
450 // the original comparison.
451 if (TCmp == FCmp)
452 return TCmp;
453
454 // The remaining cases only make sense if the select condition has the same
455 // type as the result of the comparison, so bail out if this is not so.
456 if (Cond->getType()->isVectorTy() != RHS->getType()->isVectorTy())
457 return nullptr;
458 // If the false value simplified to false, then the result of the compare
459 // is equal to "Cond && TCmp". This also catches the case when the false
460 // value simplified to false and the true value to true, returning "Cond".
461 if (match(FCmp, m_Zero()))
462 if (Value *V = SimplifyAndInst(Cond, TCmp, Q, MaxRecurse))
463 return V;
464 // If the true value simplified to true, then the result of the compare
465 // is equal to "Cond || FCmp".
466 if (match(TCmp, m_One()))
467 if (Value *V = SimplifyOrInst(Cond, FCmp, Q, MaxRecurse))
468 return V;
469 // Finally, if the false value simplified to true and the true value to
470 // false, then the result of the compare is equal to "!Cond".
471 if (match(FCmp, m_One()) && match(TCmp, m_Zero()))
472 if (Value *V =
473 SimplifyXorInst(Cond, Constant::getAllOnesValue(Cond->getType()),
474 Q, MaxRecurse))
475 return V;
476
477 return nullptr;
478}

480/// In the case of a binary operation with an operand that is a PHI instruction,
481/// try to simplify the binop by seeing whether evaluating it on the incoming
482/// phi values yields the same result for every value. If so returns the common
483/// value, otherwise returns null.
484static Value *ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *LHS,
485 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
486 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
487 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
488 if (!MaxRecurse--)
489 return nullptr;
490
491 PHINode *PI;
492 if (isa<PHINode>(LHS)) {
493 PI = cast<PHINode>(LHS);
494 // Bail out if RHS and the phi may be mutually interdependent due to a loop.
495 if (!valueDominatesPHI(RHS, PI, Q.DT))
496 return nullptr;
497 } else {
498 assert(isa<PHINode>(RHS) && "No PHI instruction operand!");
499 PI = cast<PHINode>(RHS);
500 // Bail out if LHS and the phi may be mutually interdependent due to a loop.
501 if (!valueDominatesPHI(LHS, PI, Q.DT))
502 return nullptr;
503 }
504
505 // Evaluate the BinOp on the incoming phi values.
506 Value *CommonValue = nullptr;
507 for (Value *Incoming : PI->incoming_values()) {
508 // If the incoming value is the phi node itself, it can safely be skipped.
509 if (Incoming == PI) continue;
510 Value *V = PI == LHS ?
511 SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, Incoming, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse) :
512 SimplifyBinOp(Opcode, LHS, Incoming, Q, MaxRecurse);
513 // If the operation failed to simplify, or simplified to a different value
514 // to previously, then give up.
515 if (!V || (CommonValue && V != CommonValue))
516 return nullptr;
517 CommonValue = V;
518 }
519
520 return CommonValue;
521}

523/// In the case of a comparison with a PHI instruction, try to simplify the
524/// comparison by seeing whether comparing with all of the incoming phi values
525/// yields the same result every time. If so returns the common result,
526/// otherwise returns null.
527static Value *ThreadCmpOverPHI(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
528 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
529 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
530 if (!MaxRecurse--)
531 return nullptr;
532
533 // Make sure the phi is on the LHS.
534 if (!isa<PHINode>(LHS)) {
535 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
536 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
537 }
538 assert(isa<PHINode>(LHS) && "Not comparing with a phi instruction!");
539 PHINode *PI = cast<PHINode>(LHS);
540
541 // Bail out if RHS and the phi may be mutually interdependent due to a loop.
542 if (!valueDominatesPHI(RHS, PI, Q.DT))
543 return nullptr;
544
545 // Evaluate the BinOp on the incoming phi values.
546 Value *CommonValue = nullptr;
547 for (Value *Incoming : PI->incoming_values()) {
548 // If the incoming value is the phi node itself, it can safely be skipped.
549 if (Incoming == PI) continue;
550 Value *V = SimplifyCmpInst(Pred, Incoming, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse);
551 // If the operation failed to simplify, or simplified to a different value
552 // to previously, then give up.
553 if (!V || (CommonValue && V != CommonValue))
554 return nullptr;
555 CommonValue = V;
556 }
557
558 return CommonValue;
559}

561static Constant *foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode,
562 Value *&Op0, Value *&Op1,
563 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
564 if (auto *CLHS = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op0)) {
565 if (auto *CRHS = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op1))
566 return ConstantFoldBinaryOpOperands(Opcode, CLHS, CRHS, Q.DL);
567
568 // Canonicalize the constant to the RHS if this is a commutative operation.
569 if (Instruction::isCommutative(Opcode))
570 std::swap(Op0, Op1);
571 }
572 return nullptr;
573}

575/// Given operands for an Add, see if we can fold the result.
576/// If not, this returns null.
577static Value *SimplifyAddInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool IsNSW, bool IsNUW,
578 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
579 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::Add, Op0, Op1, Q))
580 return C;
581
582 // X + undef -> undef
583 if (match(Op1, m_Undef()))
584 return Op1;
585
586 // X + 0 -> X
587 if (match(Op1, m_Zero()))
588 return Op0;
589
590 // If two operands are negative, return 0.
591 if (isKnownNegation(Op0, Op1))
592 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
593
594 // X + (Y - X) -> Y
595 // (Y - X) + X -> Y
596 // Eg: X + -X -> 0
597 Value *Y = nullptr;
598 if (match(Op1, m_Sub(m_Value(Y), m_Specific(Op0))) ||
599 match(Op0, m_Sub(m_Value(Y), m_Specific(Op1))))
600 return Y;
601
602 // X + ~X -> -1 since ~X = -X-1
603 Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
604 if (match(Op0, m_Not(m_Specific(Op1))) ||
605 match(Op1, m_Not(m_Specific(Op0))))
606 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty);
607
608 // add nsw/nuw (xor Y, signmask), signmask --> Y
609 // The no-wrapping add guarantees that the top bit will be set by the add.
610 // Therefore, the xor must be clearing the already set sign bit of Y.
611 if ((IsNSW || IsNUW) && match(Op1, m_SignMask()) &&
612 match(Op0, m_Xor(m_Value(Y), m_SignMask())))
613 return Y;
614
615 // add nuw %x, -1 -> -1, because %x can only be 0.
616 if (IsNUW && match(Op1, m_AllOnes()))
617 return Op1; // Which is -1.
618
619 /// i1 add -> xor.
620 if (MaxRecurse && Op0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1))
621 if (Value *V = SimplifyXorInst(Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
622 return V;
623
624 // Try some generic simplifications for associative operations.
625 if (Value *V = SimplifyAssociativeBinOp(Instruction::Add, Op0, Op1, Q,
626 MaxRecurse))
627 return V;
628
629 // Threading Add over selects and phi nodes is pointless, so don't bother.
630 // Threading over the select in "A + select(cond, B, C)" means evaluating
631 // "A+B" and "A+C" and seeing if they are equal; but they are equal if and
632 // only if B and C are equal. If B and C are equal then (since we assume
633 // that operands have already been simplified) "select(cond, B, C)" should
634 // have been simplified to the common value of B and C already. Analysing
635 // "A+B" and "A+C" thus gains nothing, but costs compile time. Similarly
636 // for threading over phi nodes.
637
638 return nullptr;
639}
640
641Value *llvm::SimplifyAddInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool IsNSW, bool IsNUW,
642 const SimplifyQuery &Query) {
643 return ::SimplifyAddInst(Op0, Op1, IsNSW, IsNUW, Query, RecursionLimit);
644}

646/// Compute the base pointer and cumulative constant offsets for V.
647///
648/// This strips all constant offsets off of V, leaving it the base pointer, and
649/// accumulates the total constant offset applied in the returned constant. It
650/// returns 0 if V is not a pointer, and returns the constant '0' if there are
651/// no constant offsets applied.
652///
653/// This is very similar to GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset except it doesn't
654/// follow non-inbounds geps. This allows it to remain usable for icmp ult/etc.
655/// folding.
656static Constant *stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(const DataLayout &DL, Value *&V,
657 bool AllowNonInbounds = false) {
658 assert(V->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy());
659
660 Type *IntPtrTy = DL.getIntPtrType(V->getType())->getScalarType();
661 APInt Offset = APInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy->getIntegerBitWidth());
662
663 // Even though we don't look through PHI nodes, we could be called on an
664 // instruction in an unreachable block, which may be on a cycle.
665 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> Visited;
666 Visited.insert(V);
667 do {
668 if (GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(V)) {
669 if ((!AllowNonInbounds && !GEP->isInBounds()) ||
670 !GEP->accumulateConstantOffset(DL, Offset))
671 break;
672 V = GEP->getPointerOperand();
673 } else if (Operator::getOpcode(V) == Instruction::BitCast) {
674 V = cast<Operator>(V)->getOperand(0);
675 } else if (GlobalAlias *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(V)) {
676 if (GA->isInterposable())
677 break;
678 V = GA->getAliasee();
679 } else {
680 if (auto *Call = dyn_cast<CallBase>(V))
681 if (Value *RV = Call->getReturnedArgOperand()) {
682 V = RV;
683 continue;
684 }
685 break;
686 }
687 assert(V->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && "Unexpected operand type!");
688 } while (Visited.insert(V).second);
689
690 Constant *OffsetIntPtr = ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, Offset);
691 if (V->getType()->isVectorTy())
692 return ConstantVector::getSplat(V->getType()->getVectorNumElements(),
693 OffsetIntPtr);
694 return OffsetIntPtr;
695}
696
697/// Compute the constant difference between two pointer values.
698/// If the difference is not a constant, returns zero.
699static Constant *computePointerDifference(const DataLayout &DL, Value *LHS,
700 Value *RHS) {
701 Constant *LHSOffset = stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(DL, LHS);
702 Constant *RHSOffset = stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(DL, RHS);
703
704 // If LHS and RHS are not related via constant offsets to the same base
705 // value, there is nothing we can do here.
706 if (LHS != RHS)
707 return nullptr;
708
709 // Otherwise, the difference of LHS - RHS can be computed as:
710 // LHS - RHS
711 // = (LHSOffset + Base) - (RHSOffset + Base)
712 // = LHSOffset - RHSOffset
713 return ConstantExpr::getSub(LHSOffset, RHSOffset);
714}

716/// Given operands for a Sub, see if we can fold the result.
717/// If not, this returns null.
718static Value *SimplifySubInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isNSW, bool isNUW,
719 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
720 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::Sub, Op0, Op1, Q))
721 return C;
722
723 // X - undef -> undef
724 // undef - X -> undef
725 if (match(Op0, m_Undef()) || match(Op1, m_Undef()))
726 return UndefValue::get(Op0->getType());
727
728 // X - 0 -> X
729 if (match(Op1, m_Zero()))
730 return Op0;
731
732 // X - X -> 0
733 if (Op0 == Op1)
734 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
735
736 // Is this a negation?
737 if (match(Op0, m_Zero())) {
738 // 0 - X -> 0 if the sub is NUW.
739 if (isNUW)
740 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
741
742 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Op1, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
743 if (Known.Zero.isMaxSignedValue()) {
744 // Op1 is either 0 or the minimum signed value. If the sub is NSW, then
745 // Op1 must be 0 because negating the minimum signed value is undefined.
746 if (isNSW)
747 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
748
749 // 0 - X -> X if X is 0 or the minimum signed value.
750 return Op1;
751 }
752 }
753
754 // (X + Y) - Z -> X + (Y - Z) or Y + (X - Z) if everything simplifies.
755 // For example, (X + Y) - Y -> X; (Y + X) - Y -> X
756 Value *X = nullptr, *Y = nullptr, *Z = Op1;
757 if (MaxRecurse && match(Op0, m_Add(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y)))) { // (X + Y) - Z
758 // See if "V === Y - Z" simplifies.
759 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, Y, Z, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
760 // It does! Now see if "X + V" simplifies.
761 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Add, X, V, Q, MaxRecurse-1)) {
762 // It does, we successfully reassociated!
763 ++NumReassoc;
764 return W;
765 }
766 // See if "V === X - Z" simplifies.
767 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, X, Z, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
768 // It does! Now see if "Y + V" simplifies.
769 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Add, Y, V, Q, MaxRecurse-1)) {
770 // It does, we successfully reassociated!
771 ++NumReassoc;
772 return W;
773 }
774 }
775
776 // X - (Y + Z) -> (X - Y) - Z or (X - Z) - Y if everything simplifies.
777 // For example, X - (X + 1) -> -1
778 X = Op0;
779 if (MaxRecurse && match(Op1, m_Add(m_Value(Y), m_Value(Z)))) { // X - (Y + Z)
780 // See if "V === X - Y" simplifies.
781 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, X, Y, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
782 // It does! Now see if "V - Z" simplifies.
783 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, V, Z, Q, MaxRecurse-1)) {
784 // It does, we successfully reassociated!
785 ++NumReassoc;
786 return W;
787 }
788 // See if "V === X - Z" simplifies.
789 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, X, Z, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
790 // It does! Now see if "V - Y" simplifies.
791 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, V, Y, Q, MaxRecurse-1)) {
792 // It does, we successfully reassociated!
793 ++NumReassoc;
794 return W;
795 }
796 }
797
798 // Z - (X - Y) -> (Z - X) + Y if everything simplifies.
799 // For example, X - (X - Y) -> Y.
800 Z = Op0;
801 if (MaxRecurse && match(Op1, m_Sub(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y)))) // Z - (X - Y)
802 // See if "V === Z - X" simplifies.
803 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, Z, X, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
804 // It does! Now see if "V + Y" simplifies.
805 if (Value *W = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Add, V, Y, Q, MaxRecurse-1)) {
806 // It does, we successfully reassociated!
807 ++NumReassoc;
808 return W;
809 }
810
811 // trunc(X) - trunc(Y) -> trunc(X - Y) if everything simplifies.
812 if (MaxRecurse && match(Op0, m_Trunc(m_Value(X))) &&
813 match(Op1, m_Trunc(m_Value(Y))))
814 if (X->getType() == Y->getType())
815 // See if "V === X - Y" simplifies.
816 if (Value *V = SimplifyBinOp(Instruction::Sub, X, Y, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
817 // It does! Now see if "trunc V" simplifies.
818 if (Value *W = SimplifyCastInst(Instruction::Trunc, V, Op0->getType(),
819 Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
820 // It does, return the simplified "trunc V".
821 return W;
822
823 // Variations on GEP(base, I, ...) - GEP(base, i, ...) -> GEP(null, I-i, ...).
824 if (match(Op0, m_PtrToInt(m_Value(X))) &&
825 match(Op1, m_PtrToInt(m_Value(Y))))
826 if (Constant *Result = computePointerDifference(Q.DL, X, Y))
827 return ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(Result, Op0->getType(), true);
828
829 // i1 sub -> xor.
830 if (MaxRecurse && Op0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1))
831 if (Value *V = SimplifyXorInst(Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
832 return V;
833
834 // Threading Sub over selects and phi nodes is pointless, so don't bother.
835 // Threading over the select in "A - select(cond, B, C)" means evaluating
836 // "A-B" and "A-C" and seeing if they are equal; but they are equal if and
837 // only if B and C are equal. If B and C are equal then (since we assume
838 // that operands have already been simplified) "select(cond, B, C)" should
839 // have been simplified to the common value of B and C already. Analysing
840 // "A-B" and "A-C" thus gains nothing, but costs compile time. Similarly
841 // for threading over phi nodes.
842
843 return nullptr;
844}
845
846Value *llvm::SimplifySubInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isNSW, bool isNUW,
847 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
848 return ::SimplifySubInst(Op0, Op1, isNSW, isNUW, Q, RecursionLimit);
849}

851/// Given operands for a Mul, see if we can fold the result.
852/// If not, this returns null.
853static Value *SimplifyMulInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
854 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
855 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::Mul, Op0, Op1, Q))
856 return C;
857
858 // X * undef -> 0
859 // X * 0 -> 0
860 if (match(Op1, m_CombineOr(m_Undef(), m_Zero())))
861 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
862
863 // X * 1 -> X
864 if (match(Op1, m_One()))
865 return Op0;
866
867 // (X / Y) * Y -> X if the division is exact.
868 Value *X = nullptr;
869 if (Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo &&
870 (match(Op0,
871 m_Exact(m_IDiv(m_Value(X), m_Specific(Op1)))) || // (X / Y) * Y
872 match(Op1, m_Exact(m_IDiv(m_Value(X), m_Specific(Op0)))))) // Y * (X / Y)
873 return X;
874
875 // i1 mul -> and.
876 if (MaxRecurse && Op0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1))
877 if (Value *V = SimplifyAndInst(Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
878 return V;
879
880 // Try some generic simplifications for associative operations.
881 if (Value *V = SimplifyAssociativeBinOp(Instruction::Mul, Op0, Op1, Q,
882 MaxRecurse))
883 return V;
884
885 // Mul distributes over Add. Try some generic simplifications based on this.
886 if (Value *V = ExpandBinOp(Instruction::Mul, Op0, Op1, Instruction::Add,
887 Q, MaxRecurse))
888 return V;
889
890 // If the operation is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
891 // operating on either branch of the select always yields the same value.
892 if (isa<SelectInst>(Op0) || isa<SelectInst>(Op1))
893 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Instruction::Mul, Op0, Op1, Q,
894 MaxRecurse))
895 return V;
896
897 // If the operation is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
898 // operating on all incoming values of the phi always yields the same value.
899 if (isa<PHINode>(Op0) || isa<PHINode>(Op1))
900 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Instruction::Mul, Op0, Op1, Q,
901 MaxRecurse))
902 return V;
903
904 return nullptr;
905}
906
907Value *llvm::SimplifyMulInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
908 return ::SimplifyMulInst(Op0, Op1, Q, RecursionLimit);
909}

911/// Check for common or similar folds of integer division or integer remainder.
912/// This applies to all 4 opcodes (sdiv/udiv/srem/urem).
913static Value *simplifyDivRem(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool IsDiv) {
914 Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
915
916 // X / undef -> undef
917 // X % undef -> undef
918 if (match(Op1, m_Undef()))
919 return Op1;
920
921 // X / 0 -> undef
922 // X % 0 -> undef
923 // We don't need to preserve faults!
924 if (match(Op1, m_Zero()))
925 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
926
927 // If any element of a constant divisor vector is zero or undef, the whole op
928 // is undef.
929 auto *Op1C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op1);
930 if (Op1C && Ty->isVectorTy()) {
931 unsigned NumElts = Ty->getVectorNumElements();
932 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
933 Constant *Elt = Op1C->getAggregateElement(i);
934 if (Elt && (Elt->isNullValue() || isa<UndefValue>(Elt)))
935 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
936 }
937 }
938
939 // undef / X -> 0
940 // undef % X -> 0
941 if (match(Op0, m_Undef()))
942 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
943
944 // 0 / X -> 0
945 // 0 % X -> 0
946 if (match(Op0, m_Zero()))
947 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
948
949 // X / X -> 1
950 // X % X -> 0
951 if (Op0 == Op1)
952 return IsDiv ? ConstantInt::get(Ty, 1) : Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
953
954 // X / 1 -> X
955 // X % 1 -> 0
956 // If this is a boolean op (single-bit element type), we can't have
957 // division-by-zero or remainder-by-zero, so assume the divisor is 1.
958 // Similarly, if we're zero-extending a boolean divisor, then assume it's a 1.
959 Value *X;
960 if (match(Op1, m_One()) || Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) ||
961 (match(Op1, m_ZExt(m_Value(X))) && X->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1)))
962 return IsDiv ? Op0 : Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
963
964 return nullptr;
965}
966
967/// Given a predicate and two operands, return true if the comparison is true.
968/// This is a helper for div/rem simplification where we return some other value
969/// when we can prove a relationship between the operands.
970static bool isICmpTrue(ICmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
971 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
972 Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse);
973 Constant *C = dyn_cast_or_null<Constant>(V);
974 return (C && C->isAllOnesValue());
975}
976
977/// Return true if we can simplify X / Y to 0. Remainder can adapt that answer
978/// to simplify X % Y to X.
979static bool isDivZero(Value *X, Value *Y, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
980 unsigned MaxRecurse, bool IsSigned) {
981 // Recursion is always used, so bail out at once if we already hit the limit.
982 if (!MaxRecurse--)
983 return false;
984
985 if (IsSigned) {
986 // |X| / |Y| --> 0
987 //
988 // We require that 1 operand is a simple constant. That could be extended to
989 // 2 variables if we computed the sign bit for each.
990 //
991 // Make sure that a constant is not the minimum signed value because taking
992 // the abs() of that is undefined.
993 Type *Ty = X->getType();
994 const APInt *C;
995 if (match(X, m_APInt(C)) && !C->isMinSignedValue()) {
996 // Is the variable divisor magnitude always greater than the constant
997 // dividend magnitude?
998 // |Y| > |C| --> Y < -abs(C) or Y > abs(C)
999 Constant *PosDividendC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, C->abs());
1000 Constant *NegDividendC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, -C->abs());
1001 if (isICmpTrue(CmpInst::ICMP_SLT, Y, NegDividendC, Q, MaxRecurse) ||
1002 isICmpTrue(CmpInst::ICMP_SGT, Y, PosDividendC, Q, MaxRecurse))
1003 return true;
1004 }
1005 if (match(Y, m_APInt(C))) {
1006 // Special-case: we can't take the abs() of a minimum signed value. If
1007 // that's the divisor, then all we have to do is prove that the dividend
1008 // is also not the minimum signed value.
1009 if (C->isMinSignedValue())
1010 return isICmpTrue(CmpInst::ICMP_NE, X, Y, Q, MaxRecurse);
1011
1012 // Is the variable dividend magnitude always less than the constant
1013 // divisor magnitude?
1014 // |X| < |C| --> X > -abs(C) and X < abs(C)
1015 Constant *PosDivisorC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, C->abs());
1016 Constant *NegDivisorC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, -C->abs());
1017 if (isICmpTrue(CmpInst::ICMP_SGT, X, NegDivisorC, Q, MaxRecurse) &&
1018 isICmpTrue(CmpInst::ICMP_SLT, X, PosDivisorC, Q, MaxRecurse))
1019 return true;
1020 }
1021 return false;
1022 }
1023
1024 // IsSigned == false.
1025 // Is the dividend unsigned less than the divisor?
1026 return isICmpTrue(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, X, Y, Q, MaxRecurse);
1027}
1028
1029/// These are simplifications common to SDiv and UDiv.
1030static Value *simplifyDiv(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *Op0, Value *Op1,
1031 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1032 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q))
1033 return C;
1034
1035 if (Value *V = simplifyDivRem(Op0, Op1, true))
1036 return V;
1037
1038 bool IsSigned = Opcode == Instruction::SDiv;
1039
1040 // (X * Y) / Y -> X if the multiplication does not overflow.
1041 Value *X;
1042 if (match(Op0, m_c_Mul(m_Value(X), m_Specific(Op1)))) {
1043 auto *Mul = cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(Op0);
1044 // If the Mul does not overflow, then we are good to go.
1045 if ((IsSigned && Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(Mul)) ||
1046 (!IsSigned && Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(Mul)))
1047 return X;
1048 // If X has the form X = A / Y, then X * Y cannot overflow.
1049 if ((IsSigned && match(X, m_SDiv(m_Value(), m_Specific(Op1)))) ||
1050 (!IsSigned && match(X, m_UDiv(m_Value(), m_Specific(Op1)))))
1051 return X;
1052 }
1053
1054 // (X rem Y) / Y -> 0
1055 if ((IsSigned && match(Op0, m_SRem(m_Value(), m_Specific(Op1)))) ||
1056 (!IsSigned && match(Op0, m_URem(m_Value(), m_Specific(Op1)))))
1057 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1058
1059 // (X /u C1) /u C2 -> 0 if C1 * C2 overflow
1060 ConstantInt *C1, *C2;
1061 if (!IsSigned && match(Op0, m_UDiv(m_Value(X), m_ConstantInt(C1))) &&
1062 match(Op1, m_ConstantInt(C2))) {
1063 bool Overflow;
1064 (void)C1->getValue().umul_ov(C2->getValue(), Overflow);
1065 if (Overflow)
1066 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1067 }
1068
1069 // If the operation is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
1070 // operating on either branch of the select always yields the same value.
1071 if (isa<SelectInst>(Op0) || isa<SelectInst>(Op1))
1072 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1073 return V;
1074
1075 // If the operation is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
1076 // operating on all incoming values of the phi always yields the same value.
1077 if (isa<PHINode>(Op0) || isa<PHINode>(Op1))
1078 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1079 return V;
1080
1081 if (isDivZero(Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse, IsSigned))
1082 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1083
1084 return nullptr;
1085}
1086
1087/// These are simplifications common to SRem and URem.
1088static Value *simplifyRem(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *Op0, Value *Op1,
1089 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1090 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q))
1091 return C;
1092
1093 if (Value *V = simplifyDivRem(Op0, Op1, false))
1094 return V;
1095
1096 // (X % Y) % Y -> X % Y
1097 if ((Opcode == Instruction::SRem &&
1098 match(Op0, m_SRem(m_Value(), m_Specific(Op1)))) ||
1099 (Opcode == Instruction::URem &&
1100 match(Op0, m_URem(m_Value(), m_Specific(Op1)))))
1101 return Op0;
1102
1103 // (X << Y) % X -> 0
1104 if (Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo &&
1105 ((Opcode == Instruction::SRem &&
1106 match(Op0, m_NSWShl(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value()))) ||
1107 (Opcode == Instruction::URem &&
1108 match(Op0, m_NUWShl(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value())))))
1109 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1110
1111 // If the operation is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
1112 // operating on either branch of the select always yields the same value.
1113 if (isa<SelectInst>(Op0) || isa<SelectInst>(Op1))
1114 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1115 return V;
1116
1117 // If the operation is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
1118 // operating on all incoming values of the phi always yields the same value.
1119 if (isa<PHINode>(Op0) || isa<PHINode>(Op1))
1120 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1121 return V;
1122
1123 // If X / Y == 0, then X % Y == X.
1124 if (isDivZero(Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse, Opcode == Instruction::SRem))
1125 return Op0;
1126
1127 return nullptr;
1128}

1130/// Given operands for an SDiv, see if we can fold the result.
1131/// If not, this returns null.
1132static Value *SimplifySDivInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
1133 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1134 // If two operands are negated and no signed overflow, return -1.
1135 if (isKnownNegation(Op0, Op1, /*NeedNSW=*/true))
1136 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
1137
1138 return simplifyDiv(Instruction::SDiv, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse);
1139}
1140
1141Value *llvm::SimplifySDivInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {

1156/// Given operands for an SRem, see if we can fold the result.
1157/// If not, this returns null.
1158static Value *SimplifySRemInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
1159 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1160 // If the divisor is 0, the result is undefined, so assume the divisor is -1.
1161 // srem Op0, (sext i1 X) --> srem Op0, -1 --> 0
1162 Value *X;
1163 if (match(Op1, m_SExt(m_Value(X))) && X->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1))
1164 return ConstantInt::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1165
1166 // If the two operands are negated, return 0.
1167 if (isKnownNegation(Op0, Op1))
1168 return ConstantInt::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1169
1170 return simplifyRem(Instruction::SRem, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse);
1171}

1188/// Returns true if a shift by \c Amount always yields undef.
1189static bool isUndefShift(Value *Amount) {
1190 Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Amount);
1191 if (!C)
1192 return false;
1193
1194 // X shift by undef -> undef because it may shift by the bitwidth.
1195 if (isa<UndefValue>(C))
1196 return true;
1197
1198 // Shifting by the bitwidth or more is undefined.
1199 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(C))
1200 if (CI->getValue().getLimitedValue() >=
1201 CI->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits())
1202 return true;
1203
1204 // If all lanes of a vector shift are undefined the whole shift is.
1205 if (isa<ConstantVector>(C) || isa<ConstantDataVector>(C)) {
1206 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getType()->getVectorNumElements(); I != E; ++I)
1207 if (!isUndefShift(C->getAggregateElement(I)))
1208 return false;
1209 return true;
1210 }
1211
1212 return false;
1213}

1215/// Given operands for an Shl, LShr or AShr, see if we can fold the result.
1216/// If not, this returns null.
1217static Value *SimplifyShift(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *Op0,
1218 Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1219 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q))
1220 return C;
1221
1222 // 0 shift by X -> 0
1223 if (match(Op0, m_Zero()))
1224 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1225
1226 // X shift by 0 -> X
1227 // Shift-by-sign-extended bool must be shift-by-0 because shift-by-all-ones
1228 // would be poison.
1229 Value *X;
1230 if (match(Op1, m_Zero()) ||
1231 (match(Op1, m_SExt(m_Value(X))) && X->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1)))
1232 return Op0;
1233
1234 // Fold undefined shifts.
1235 if (isUndefShift(Op1))
1236 return UndefValue::get(Op0->getType());
1237
1238 // If the operation is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
1239 // operating on either branch of the select always yields the same value.
1240 if (isa<SelectInst>(Op0) || isa<SelectInst>(Op1))
1241 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1242 return V;
1243
1244 // If the operation is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
1245 // operating on all incoming values of the phi always yields the same value.
1246 if (isa<PHINode>(Op0) || isa<PHINode>(Op1))
1247 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1248 return V;
1249
1250 // If any bits in the shift amount make that value greater than or equal to
1251 // the number of bits in the type, the shift is undefined.
1252 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Op1, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
1253 if (Known.One.getLimitedValue() >= Known.getBitWidth())
1254 return UndefValue::get(Op0->getType());
1255
1256 // If all valid bits in the shift amount are known zero, the first operand is
1257 // unchanged.
1258 unsigned NumValidShiftBits = Log2_32_Ceil(Known.getBitWidth());
1259 if (Known.countMinTrailingZeros() >= NumValidShiftBits)
1260 return Op0;
1261
1262 return nullptr;
1263}
1264
1265/// Given operands for an Shl, LShr or AShr, see if we can
1266/// fold the result. If not, this returns null.
1267static Value *SimplifyRightShift(Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode, Value *Op0,
1268 Value *Op1, bool isExact, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
1269 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1270 if (Value *V = SimplifyShift(Opcode, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1271 return V;
1272
1273 // X >> X -> 0
1274 if (Op0 == Op1)
1275 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1276
1277 // undef >> X -> 0
1278 // undef >> X -> undef (if it's exact)
1279 if (match(Op0, m_Undef()))
1280 return isExact ? Op0 : Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1281
1282 // The low bit cannot be shifted out of an exact shift if it is set.
1283 if (isExact) {
1284 KnownBits Op0Known = computeKnownBits(Op0, Q.DL, /*Depth=*/0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
1285 if (Op0Known.One[0])
1286 return Op0;
1287 }
1288
1289 return nullptr;
1290}

1292/// Given operands for an Shl, see if we can fold the result.
1293/// If not, this returns null.
1294static Value *SimplifyShlInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isNSW, bool isNUW,
1295 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1296 if (Value *V = SimplifyShift(Instruction::Shl, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
1297 return V;
1298
1299 // undef << X -> 0
1300 // undef << X -> undef if (if it's NSW/NUW)
1301 if (match(Op0, m_Undef()))
1302 return isNSW || isNUW ? Op0 : Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1303
1304 // (X >> A) << A -> X
1305 Value *X;
1306 if (Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo &&
1307 match(Op0, m_Exact(m_Shr(m_Value(X), m_Specific(Op1)))))
1308 return X;
1309
1310 // shl nuw i8 C, %x -> C iff C has sign bit set.
1311 if (isNUW && match(Op0, m_Negative()))
1312 return Op0;
1313 // NOTE: could use computeKnownBits() / LazyValueInfo,
1314 // but the cost-benefit analysis suggests it isn't worth it.
1315
1316 return nullptr;
1317}

1319Value *llvm::SimplifyShlInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isNSW, bool isNUW,
1320 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
1321 return ::SimplifyShlInst(Op0, Op1, isNSW, isNUW, Q, RecursionLimit);
1322}

1324/// Given operands for an LShr, see if we can fold the result.
1325/// If not, this returns null.
1326static Value *SimplifyLShrInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isExact,
1327 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1328 if (Value *V = SimplifyRightShift(Instruction::LShr, Op0, Op1, isExact, Q,
1329 MaxRecurse))
1330 return V;
1331
1332 // (X << A) >> A -> X
1333 Value *X;
1334 if (match(Op0, m_NUWShl(m_Value(X), m_Specific(Op1))))
1335 return X;
1336
1337 // ((X << A) | Y) >> A -> X if effective width of Y is not larger than A.
1338 // We can return X as we do in the above case since OR alters no bits in X.
1339 // SimplifyDemandedBits in InstCombine can do more general optimization for
1340 // bit manipulation. This pattern aims to provide opportunities for other
1341 // optimizers by supporting a simple but common case in InstSimplify.
1342 Value *Y;
1343 const APInt *ShRAmt, *ShLAmt;
1344 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(ShRAmt)) &&
1345 match(Op0, m_c_Or(m_NUWShl(m_Value(X), m_APInt(ShLAmt)), m_Value(Y))) &&
1346 *ShRAmt == *ShLAmt) {
1347 const KnownBits YKnown = computeKnownBits(Y, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
1348 const unsigned Width = Op0->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1349 const unsigned EffWidthY = Width - YKnown.countMinLeadingZeros();
1350 if (ShRAmt->uge(EffWidthY))
1351 return X;
1352 }
1353
1354 return nullptr;
1355}
1356
1357Value *llvm::SimplifyLShrInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isExact,
1358 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
1359 return ::SimplifyLShrInst(Op0, Op1, isExact, Q, RecursionLimit);
1360}

1362/// Given operands for an AShr, see if we can fold the result.
1363/// If not, this returns null.
1364static Value *SimplifyAShrInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool isExact,
1365 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1366 if (Value *V = SimplifyRightShift(Instruction::AShr, Op0, Op1, isExact, Q,
1367 MaxRecurse))
1368 return V;
1369
1370 // all ones >>a X -> -1
1371 // Do not return Op0 because it may contain undef elements if it's a vector.
1372 if (match(Op0, m_AllOnes()))
1373 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
1374
1375 // (X << A) >> A -> X
1376 Value *X;
1377 if (Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo && match(Op0, m_NSWShl(m_Value(X), m_Specific(Op1))))
1378 return X;
1379
1380 // Arithmetic shifting an all-sign-bit value is a no-op.
1381 unsigned NumSignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Op0, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
1382 if (NumSignBits == Op0->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits())
1383 return Op0;
1384
1385 return nullptr;
1386}

1389 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
1390 return ::SimplifyAShrInst(Op0, Op1, isExact, Q, RecursionLimit);
1391}

1393/// Commuted variants are assumed to be handled by calling this function again
1394/// with the parameters swapped.
1395static Value *simplifyUnsignedRangeCheck(ICmpInst *ZeroICmp,
1396 ICmpInst *UnsignedICmp, bool IsAnd) {
1397 Value *X, *Y;
1398
1399 ICmpInst::Predicate EqPred;
1400 if (!match(ZeroICmp, m_ICmp(EqPred, m_Value(Y), m_Zero())) ||
1401 !ICmpInst::isEquality(EqPred))
1402 return nullptr;
1403
1404 ICmpInst::Predicate UnsignedPred;
1405 if (match(UnsignedICmp, m_ICmp(UnsignedPred, m_Value(X), m_Specific(Y))) &&
1406 ICmpInst::isUnsigned(UnsignedPred))
1407 ;
1408 else if (match(UnsignedICmp,
1409 m_ICmp(UnsignedPred, m_Specific(Y), m_Value(X))) &&
1410 ICmpInst::isUnsigned(UnsignedPred))
1411 UnsignedPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(UnsignedPred);
1412 else
1413 return nullptr;
1414
1415 // X < Y && Y != 0 --> X < Y
1416 // X < Y || Y != 0 --> Y != 0
1417 if (UnsignedPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && EqPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
1418 return IsAnd ? UnsignedICmp : ZeroICmp;
1419
1420 // X >= Y || Y != 0 --> true
1421 // X >= Y || Y == 0 --> X >= Y
1422 if (UnsignedPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE && !IsAnd) {
1423 if (EqPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
1424 return getTrue(UnsignedICmp->getType());
1425 return UnsignedICmp;
1426 }
1427
1428 // X < Y && Y == 0 --> false
1429 if (UnsignedPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && EqPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ &&
1430 IsAnd)
1431 return getFalse(UnsignedICmp->getType());
1432
1433 return nullptr;
1434}
1435
1436/// Commuted variants are assumed to be handled by calling this function again
1437/// with the parameters swapped.
1438static Value *simplifyAndOfICmpsWithSameOperands(ICmpInst *Op0, ICmpInst *Op1) {
1439 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred0, Pred1;
1440 Value *A ,*B;
1441 if (!match(Op0, m_ICmp(Pred0, m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) ||
1442 !match(Op1, m_ICmp(Pred1, m_Specific(A), m_Specific(B))))
1443 return nullptr;
1444
1445 // We have (icmp Pred0, A, B) & (icmp Pred1, A, B).
1446 // If Op1 is always implied true by Op0, then Op0 is a subset of Op1, and we
1447 // can eliminate Op1 from this 'and'.
1448 if (ICmpInst::isImpliedTrueByMatchingCmp(Pred0, Pred1))
1449 return Op0;
1450
1451 // Check for any combination of predicates that are guaranteed to be disjoint.
1452 if ((Pred0 == ICmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred1)) ||
1453 (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ && ICmpInst::isFalseWhenEqual(Pred1)) ||
1454 (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT) ||
1455 (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT))
1456 return getFalse(Op0->getType());
1457
1458 return nullptr;
1459}
1460
1461/// Commuted variants are assumed to be handled by calling this function again
1462/// with the parameters swapped.
1463static Value *simplifyOrOfICmpsWithSameOperands(ICmpInst *Op0, ICmpInst *Op1) {
1464 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred0, Pred1;
1465 Value *A ,*B;
1466 if (!match(Op0, m_ICmp(Pred0, m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) ||
1467 !match(Op1, m_ICmp(Pred1, m_Specific(A), m_Specific(B))))
1468 return nullptr;
1469
1470 // We have (icmp Pred0, A, B) | (icmp Pred1, A, B).
1471 // If Op1 is always implied true by Op0, then Op0 is a subset of Op1, and we
1472 // can eliminate Op0 from this 'or'.
1473 if (ICmpInst::isImpliedTrueByMatchingCmp(Pred0, Pred1))
1474 return Op1;
1475
1476 // Check for any combination of predicates that cover the entire range of
1477 // possibilities.
1478 if ((Pred0 == ICmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred1)) ||
1479 (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE && ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred1)) ||
1480 (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE) ||
1481 (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE))
1482 return getTrue(Op0->getType());
1483
1484 return nullptr;
1485}
1486
1487/// Test if a pair of compares with a shared operand and 2 constants has an
1488/// empty set intersection, full set union, or if one compare is a superset of
1489/// the other.
1490static Value *simplifyAndOrOfICmpsWithConstants(ICmpInst *Cmp0, ICmpInst *Cmp1,
1491 bool IsAnd) {
1492 // Look for this pattern: {and/or} (icmp X, C0), (icmp X, C1)).
1493 if (Cmp0->getOperand(0) != Cmp1->getOperand(0))
1494 return nullptr;
1495
1496 const APInt *C0, *C1;
1497 if (!match(Cmp0->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C0)) ||
1498 !match(Cmp1->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C1)))
1499 return nullptr;
1500
1501 auto Range0 = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(Cmp0->getPredicate(), *C0);
1502 auto Range1 = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(Cmp1->getPredicate(), *C1);
1503
1504 // For and-of-compares, check if the intersection is empty:
1505 // (icmp X, C0) && (icmp X, C1) --> empty set --> false
1506 if (IsAnd && Range0.intersectWith(Range1).isEmptySet())
1507 return getFalse(Cmp0->getType());
1508
1509 // For or-of-compares, check if the union is full:
1510 // (icmp X, C0) || (icmp X, C1) --> full set --> true
1511 if (!IsAnd && Range0.unionWith(Range1).isFullSet())
1512 return getTrue(Cmp0->getType());
1513
1514 // Is one range a superset of the other?
1515 // If this is and-of-compares, take the smaller set:
1516 // (icmp sgt X, 4) && (icmp sgt X, 42) --> icmp sgt X, 42
1517 // If this is or-of-compares, take the larger set:
1518 // (icmp sgt X, 4) || (icmp sgt X, 42) --> icmp sgt X, 4
1519 if (Range0.contains(Range1))
1520 return IsAnd ? Cmp1 : Cmp0;
1521 if (Range1.contains(Range0))
1522 return IsAnd ? Cmp0 : Cmp1;
1523
1524 return nullptr;
1525}
1526
1527static Value *simplifyAndOrOfICmpsWithZero(ICmpInst *Cmp0, ICmpInst *Cmp1,
1528 bool IsAnd) {
1529 ICmpInst::Predicate P0 = Cmp0->getPredicate(), P1 = Cmp1->getPredicate();
1530 if (!match(Cmp0->getOperand(1), m_Zero()) ||
1531 !match(Cmp1->getOperand(1), m_Zero()) || P0 != P1)
1532 return nullptr;
1533
1534 if ((IsAnd && P0 != ICmpInst::ICMP_NE) || (!IsAnd && P1 != ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ))
1535 return nullptr;
1536
1537 // We have either "(X == 0 || Y == 0)" or "(X != 0 && Y != 0)".
1538 Value *X = Cmp0->getOperand(0);
1539 Value *Y = Cmp1->getOperand(0);
1540
1541 // If one of the compares is a masked version of a (not) null check, then
1542 // that compare implies the other, so we eliminate the other. Optionally, look
1543 // through a pointer-to-int cast to match a null check of a pointer type.
1544
1545 // (X == 0) || (([ptrtoint] X & ?) == 0) --> ([ptrtoint] X & ?) == 0
1546 // (X == 0) || ((? & [ptrtoint] X) == 0) --> (? & [ptrtoint] X) == 0
1547 // (X != 0) && (([ptrtoint] X & ?) != 0) --> ([ptrtoint] X & ?) != 0
1548 // (X != 0) && ((? & [ptrtoint] X) != 0) --> (? & [ptrtoint] X) != 0
1549 if (match(Y, m_c_And(m_Specific(X), m_Value())) ||
1550 match(Y, m_c_And(m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(X)), m_Value())))
1551 return Cmp1;
1552
1553 // (([ptrtoint] Y & ?) == 0) || (Y == 0) --> ([ptrtoint] Y & ?) == 0
1554 // ((? & [ptrtoint] Y) == 0) || (Y == 0) --> (? & [ptrtoint] Y) == 0
1555 // (([ptrtoint] Y & ?) != 0) && (Y != 0) --> ([ptrtoint] Y & ?) != 0
1556 // ((? & [ptrtoint] Y) != 0) && (Y != 0) --> (? & [ptrtoint] Y) != 0
1557 if (match(X, m_c_And(m_Specific(Y), m_Value())) ||
1558 match(X, m_c_And(m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(Y)), m_Value())))
1559 return Cmp0;
1560
1561 return nullptr;
1562}
1563
1564static Value *simplifyAndOfICmpsWithAdd(ICmpInst *Op0, ICmpInst *Op1,
1565 const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
1566 // (icmp (add V, C0), C1) & (icmp V, C0)
1567 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred0, Pred1;
1568 const APInt *C0, *C1;
1569 Value *V;
1570 if (!match(Op0, m_ICmp(Pred0, m_Add(m_Value(V), m_APInt(C0)), m_APInt(C1))))
1571 return nullptr;
1572
1573 if (!match(Op1, m_ICmp(Pred1, m_Specific(V), m_Value())))
1574 return nullptr;
1575
1576 auto *AddInst = cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(Op0->getOperand(0));
1577 if (AddInst->getOperand(1) != Op1->getOperand(1))
1578 return nullptr;
1579
1580 Type *ITy = Op0->getType();
1581 bool isNSW = IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(AddInst);
1582 bool isNUW = IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(AddInst);
1583
1584 const APInt Delta = *C1 - *C0;
1585 if (C0->isStrictlyPositive()) {
1586 if (Delta == 2) {
1587 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
1588 return getFalse(ITy);
1589 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && isNSW)
1590 return getFalse(ITy);
1591 }
1592 if (Delta == 1) {
1593 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
1594 return getFalse(ITy);
1595 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && isNSW)
1596 return getFalse(ITy);
1597 }
1598 }
1599 if (C0->getBoolValue() && isNUW) {
1600 if (Delta == 2)
1601 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
1602 return getFalse(ITy);
1603 if (Delta == 1)
1604 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
1605 return getFalse(ITy);
1606 }
1607
1608 return nullptr;
1609}
1610
1611static Value *simplifyAndOfICmps(ICmpInst *Op0, ICmpInst *Op1,
1612 const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
1613 if (Value *X = simplifyUnsignedRangeCheck(Op0, Op1, /*IsAnd=*/true))
1614 return X;
1615 if (Value *X = simplifyUnsignedRangeCheck(Op1, Op0, /*IsAnd=*/true))
1616 return X;
1617
1618 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOfICmpsWithSameOperands(Op0, Op1))
1619 return X;
1620 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOfICmpsWithSameOperands(Op1, Op0))
1621 return X;
1622
1623 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOrOfICmpsWithConstants(Op0, Op1, true))
1624 return X;
1625
1626 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOrOfICmpsWithZero(Op0, Op1, true))
1627 return X;
1628
1629 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOfICmpsWithAdd(Op0, Op1, IIQ))
1630 return X;
1631 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOfICmpsWithAdd(Op1, Op0, IIQ))
1632 return X;
1633
1634 return nullptr;
1635}
1636
1637static Value *simplifyOrOfICmpsWithAdd(ICmpInst *Op0, ICmpInst *Op1,
1638 const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
1639 // (icmp (add V, C0), C1) | (icmp V, C0)
1640 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred0, Pred1;
1641 const APInt *C0, *C1;
1642 Value *V;
1643 if (!match(Op0, m_ICmp(Pred0, m_Add(m_Value(V), m_APInt(C0)), m_APInt(C1))))
1644 return nullptr;
1645
1646 if (!match(Op1, m_ICmp(Pred1, m_Specific(V), m_Value())))
1647 return nullptr;
1648
1649 auto *AddInst = cast<BinaryOperator>(Op0->getOperand(0));
1650 if (AddInst->getOperand(1) != Op1->getOperand(1))
1651 return nullptr;
1652
1653 Type *ITy = Op0->getType();
1654 bool isNSW = IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(AddInst);
1655 bool isNUW = IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(AddInst);
1656
1657 const APInt Delta = *C1 - *C0;
1658 if (C0->isStrictlyPositive()) {
1659 if (Delta == 2) {
1660 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
1661 return getTrue(ITy);
1662 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE && isNSW)
1663 return getTrue(ITy);
1664 }
1665 if (Delta == 1) {
1666 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
1667 return getTrue(ITy);
1668 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE && isNSW)
1669 return getTrue(ITy);
1670 }
1671 }
1672 if (C0->getBoolValue() && isNUW) {
1673 if (Delta == 2)
1674 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
1675 return getTrue(ITy);
1676 if (Delta == 1)
1677 if (Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
1678 return getTrue(ITy);
1679 }
1680
1681 return nullptr;
1682}
1683
1684static Value *simplifyOrOfICmps(ICmpInst *Op0, ICmpInst *Op1,
1685 const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
1686 if (Value *X = simplifyUnsignedRangeCheck(Op0, Op1, /*IsAnd=*/false))
1687 return X;
1688 if (Value *X = simplifyUnsignedRangeCheck(Op1, Op0, /*IsAnd=*/false))
1689 return X;
1690
1691 if (Value *X = simplifyOrOfICmpsWithSameOperands(Op0, Op1))
1692 return X;
1693 if (Value *X = simplifyOrOfICmpsWithSameOperands(Op1, Op0))
1694 return X;
1695
1696 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOrOfICmpsWithConstants(Op0, Op1, false))
1697 return X;
1698
1699 if (Value *X = simplifyAndOrOfICmpsWithZero(Op0, Op1, false))
1700 return X;
1701
1702 if (Value *X = simplifyOrOfICmpsWithAdd(Op0, Op1, IIQ))
1703 return X;
1704 if (Value *X = simplifyOrOfICmpsWithAdd(Op1, Op0, IIQ))
1705 return X;
1706
1707 return nullptr;
1708}
1709
1710static Value *simplifyAndOrOfFCmps(const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
1711 FCmpInst *LHS, FCmpInst *RHS, bool IsAnd) {
1712 Value *LHS0 = LHS->getOperand(0), *LHS1 = LHS->getOperand(1);
1713 Value *RHS0 = RHS->getOperand(0), *RHS1 = RHS->getOperand(1);
1714 if (LHS0->getType() != RHS0->getType())
1715 return nullptr;
1716
1717 FCmpInst::Predicate PredL = LHS->getPredicate(), PredR = RHS->getPredicate();
1718 if ((PredL == FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD && PredR == FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD && IsAnd) ||
1719 (PredL == FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO && PredR == FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO && !IsAnd)) {
1720 // (fcmp ord NNAN, X) & (fcmp ord X, Y) --> fcmp ord X, Y
1721 // (fcmp ord NNAN, X) & (fcmp ord Y, X) --> fcmp ord Y, X
1722 // (fcmp ord X, NNAN) & (fcmp ord X, Y) --> fcmp ord X, Y
1723 // (fcmp ord X, NNAN) & (fcmp ord Y, X) --> fcmp ord Y, X
1724 // (fcmp uno NNAN, X) | (fcmp uno X, Y) --> fcmp uno X, Y
1725 // (fcmp uno NNAN, X) | (fcmp uno Y, X) --> fcmp uno Y, X
1726 // (fcmp uno X, NNAN) | (fcmp uno X, Y) --> fcmp uno X, Y
1727 // (fcmp uno X, NNAN) | (fcmp uno Y, X) --> fcmp uno Y, X
1728 if ((isKnownNeverNaN(LHS0, TLI) && (LHS1 == RHS0 || LHS1 == RHS1)) ||
1729 (isKnownNeverNaN(LHS1, TLI) && (LHS0 == RHS0 || LHS0 == RHS1)))
1730 return RHS;
1731
1732 // (fcmp ord X, Y) & (fcmp ord NNAN, X) --> fcmp ord X, Y
1733 // (fcmp ord Y, X) & (fcmp ord NNAN, X) --> fcmp ord Y, X
1734 // (fcmp ord X, Y) & (fcmp ord X, NNAN) --> fcmp ord X, Y
1735 // (fcmp ord Y, X) & (fcmp ord X, NNAN) --> fcmp ord Y, X
1736 // (fcmp uno X, Y) | (fcmp uno NNAN, X) --> fcmp uno X, Y
1737 // (fcmp uno Y, X) | (fcmp uno NNAN, X) --> fcmp uno Y, X
1738 // (fcmp uno X, Y) | (fcmp uno X, NNAN) --> fcmp uno X, Y
1739 // (fcmp uno Y, X) | (fcmp uno X, NNAN) --> fcmp uno Y, X
1740 if ((isKnownNeverNaN(RHS0, TLI) && (RHS1 == LHS0 || RHS1 == LHS1)) ||
1741 (isKnownNeverNaN(RHS1, TLI) && (RHS0 == LHS0 || RHS0 == LHS1)))
1742 return LHS;
1743 }
1744
1745 return nullptr;
1746}
1747
1748static Value *simplifyAndOrOfCmps(const SimplifyQuery &Q,
1749 Value *Op0, Value *Op1, bool IsAnd) {
1750 // Look through casts of the 'and' operands to find compares.
1751 auto *Cast0 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(Op0);
1752 auto *Cast1 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(Op1);
1753 if (Cast0 && Cast1 && Cast0->getOpcode() == Cast1->getOpcode() &&
1754 Cast0->getSrcTy() == Cast1->getSrcTy()) {
1755 Op0 = Cast0->getOperand(0);
1756 Op1 = Cast1->getOperand(0);
1757 }
1758
1759 Value *V = nullptr;
1760 auto *ICmp0 = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Op0);
1761 auto *ICmp1 = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Op1);
1762 if (ICmp0 && ICmp1)
1763 V = IsAnd ? simplifyAndOfICmps(ICmp0, ICmp1, Q.IIQ)
1764 : simplifyOrOfICmps(ICmp0, ICmp1, Q.IIQ);
1765
1766 auto *FCmp0 = dyn_cast<FCmpInst>(Op0);
1767 auto *FCmp1 = dyn_cast<FCmpInst>(Op1);
1768 if (FCmp0 && FCmp1)
1769 V = simplifyAndOrOfFCmps(Q.TLI, FCmp0, FCmp1, IsAnd);
1770
1771 if (!V)
1772 return nullptr;
1773 if (!Cast0)
1774 return V;
1775
1776 // If we looked through casts, we can only handle a constant simplification
1777 // because we are not allowed to create a cast instruction here.
1778 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V))
1779 return ConstantExpr::getCast(Cast0->getOpcode(), C, Cast0->getType());
1780
1781 return nullptr;
1782}

1784/// Given operands for an And, see if we can fold the result.
1785/// If not, this returns null.
1786static Value *SimplifyAndInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
1787 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1788 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::And, Op0, Op1, Q))
1789 return C;
1790
1791 // X & undef -> 0
1792 if (match(Op1, m_Undef()))
1793 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1794
1795 // X & X = X
1796 if (Op0 == Op1)
1797 return Op0;
1798
1799 // X & 0 = 0
1800 if (match(Op1, m_Zero()))
1801 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1802
1803 // X & -1 = X
1804 if (match(Op1, m_AllOnes()))
1805 return Op0;
1806
1807 // A & ~A = ~A & A = 0
1808 if (match(Op0, m_Not(m_Specific(Op1))) ||
1809 match(Op1, m_Not(m_Specific(Op0))))
1810 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1811
1812 // (A | ?) & A = A
1813 if (match(Op0, m_c_Or(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value())))
1814 return Op1;
1815
1816 // A & (A | ?) = A
1817 if (match(Op1, m_c_Or(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value())))
1818 return Op0;
1819
1820 // A mask that only clears known zeros of a shifted value is a no-op.
1821 Value *X;
1822 const APInt *Mask;
1823 const APInt *ShAmt;
1824 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(Mask))) {
1825 // If all bits in the inverted and shifted mask are clear:
1826 // and (shl X, ShAmt), Mask --> shl X, ShAmt
1827 if (match(Op0, m_Shl(m_Value(X), m_APInt(ShAmt))) &&
1828 (~(*Mask)).lshr(*ShAmt).isNullValue())
1829 return Op0;
1830
1831 // If all bits in the inverted and shifted mask are clear:
1832 // and (lshr X, ShAmt), Mask --> lshr X, ShAmt
1833 if (match(Op0, m_LShr(m_Value(X), m_APInt(ShAmt))) &&
1834 (~(*Mask)).shl(*ShAmt).isNullValue())
1835 return Op0;
1836 }
1837
1838 // A & (-A) = A if A is a power of two or zero.
1839 if (match(Op0, m_Neg(m_Specific(Op1))) ||
1840 match(Op1, m_Neg(m_Specific(Op0)))) {
1841 if (isKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo(Op0, Q.DL, /*OrZero*/ true, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI,
1842 Q.DT))
1843 return Op0;
1844 if (isKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo(Op1, Q.DL, /*OrZero*/ true, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI,
1845 Q.DT))
1846 return Op1;
1847 }
1848
1849 if (Value *V = simplifyAndOrOfCmps(Q, Op0, Op1, true))
1850 return V;
1851
1852 // Try some generic simplifications for associative operations.
1853 if (Value *V = SimplifyAssociativeBinOp(Instruction::And, Op0, Op1, Q,
1854 MaxRecurse))
1855 return V;
1856
1857 // And distributes over Or. Try some generic simplifications based on this.
1858 if (Value *V = ExpandBinOp(Instruction::And, Op0, Op1, Instruction::Or,
1859 Q, MaxRecurse))
1860 return V;
1861
1862 // And distributes over Xor. Try some generic simplifications based on this.
1863 if (Value *V = ExpandBinOp(Instruction::And, Op0, Op1, Instruction::Xor,
1864 Q, MaxRecurse))
1865 return V;
1866
1867 // If the operation is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
1868 // operating on either branch of the select always yields the same value.
1869 if (isa<SelectInst>(Op0) || isa<SelectInst>(Op1))
1870 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Instruction::And, Op0, Op1, Q,
1871 MaxRecurse))
1872 return V;
1873
1874 // If the operation is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
1875 // operating on all incoming values of the phi always yields the same value.
1876 if (isa<PHINode>(Op0) || isa<PHINode>(Op1))
1877 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Instruction::And, Op0, Op1, Q,
1878 MaxRecurse))
1879 return V;
1880
1881 // Assuming the effective width of Y is not larger than A, i.e. all bits
1882 // from X and Y are disjoint in (X << A) | Y,
1883 // if the mask of this AND op covers all bits of X or Y, while it covers
1884 // no bits from the other, we can bypass this AND op. E.g.,
1885 // ((X << A) | Y) & Mask -> Y,
1886 // if Mask = ((1 << effective_width_of(Y)) - 1)
1887 // ((X << A) | Y) & Mask -> X << A,
1888 // if Mask = ((1 << effective_width_of(X)) - 1) << A
1889 // SimplifyDemandedBits in InstCombine can optimize the general case.
1890 // This pattern aims to help other passes for a common case.
1891 Value *Y, *XShifted;
1892 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(Mask)) &&
1893 match(Op0, m_c_Or(m_CombineAnd(m_NUWShl(m_Value(X), m_APInt(ShAmt)),
1894 m_Value(XShifted)),
1895 m_Value(Y)))) {
1896 const unsigned Width = Op0->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1897 const unsigned ShftCnt = ShAmt->getLimitedValue(Width);
1898 const KnownBits YKnown = computeKnownBits(Y, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
1899 const unsigned EffWidthY = Width - YKnown.countMinLeadingZeros();
1900 if (EffWidthY <= ShftCnt) {
1901 const KnownBits XKnown = computeKnownBits(X, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI,
1902 Q.DT);
1903 const unsigned EffWidthX = Width - XKnown.countMinLeadingZeros();
1904 const APInt EffBitsY = APInt::getLowBitsSet(Width, EffWidthY);
1905 const APInt EffBitsX = APInt::getLowBitsSet(Width, EffWidthX) << ShftCnt;
1906 // If the mask is extracting all bits from X or Y as is, we can skip
1907 // this AND op.
1908 if (EffBitsY.isSubsetOf(*Mask) && !EffBitsX.intersects(*Mask))
1909 return Y;
1910 if (EffBitsX.isSubsetOf(*Mask) && !EffBitsY.intersects(*Mask))
1911 return XShifted;
1912 }
1913 }
1914
1915 return nullptr;
1916}

1918Value *llvm::SimplifyAndInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
1919 return ::SimplifyAndInst(Op0, Op1, Q, RecursionLimit);

1922/// Given operands for an Or, see if we can fold the result.
1923/// If not, this returns null.
1924static Value *SimplifyOrInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
1925 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
1926 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::Or, Op0, Op1, Q))
1927 return C;
1928
1929 // X | undef -> -1
1930 // X | -1 = -1
1931 // Do not return Op1 because it may contain undef elements if it's a vector.
1932 if (match(Op1, m_Undef()) || match(Op1, m_AllOnes()))
1933 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
1934
1935 // X | X = X
1936 // X | 0 = X
1937 if (Op0 == Op1 || match(Op1, m_Zero()))
1938 return Op0;
1939
1940 // A | ~A = ~A | A = -1
1941 if (match(Op0, m_Not(m_Specific(Op1))) ||
1942 match(Op1, m_Not(m_Specific(Op0))))
1943 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
1944
1945 // (A & ?) | A = A
1946 if (match(Op0, m_c_And(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value())))
1947 return Op1;
1948
1949 // A | (A & ?) = A
1950 if (match(Op1, m_c_And(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value())))
1951 return Op0;
1952
1953 // ~(A & ?) | A = -1
1954 if (match(Op0, m_Not(m_c_And(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value()))))
1955 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op1->getType());
1956
1957 // A | ~(A & ?) = -1
1958 if (match(Op1, m_Not(m_c_And(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value()))))
1959 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
1960
1961 Value *A, *B;
1962 // (A & ~B) | (A ^ B) -> (A ^ B)
1963 // (~B & A) | (A ^ B) -> (A ^ B)
1964 // (A & ~B) | (B ^ A) -> (B ^ A)
1965 // (~B & A) | (B ^ A) -> (B ^ A)
1966 if (match(Op1, m_Xor(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
1967 (match(Op0, m_c_And(m_Specific(A), m_Not(m_Specific(B)))) ||
1968 match(Op0, m_c_And(m_Not(m_Specific(A)), m_Specific(B)))))
1969 return Op1;
1970
1971 // Commute the 'or' operands.
1972 // (A ^ B) | (A & ~B) -> (A ^ B)
1973 // (A ^ B) | (~B & A) -> (A ^ B)
1974 // (B ^ A) | (A & ~B) -> (B ^ A)
1975 // (B ^ A) | (~B & A) -> (B ^ A)
1976 if (match(Op0, m_Xor(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
1977 (match(Op1, m_c_And(m_Specific(A), m_Not(m_Specific(B)))) ||
1978 match(Op1, m_c_And(m_Not(m_Specific(A)), m_Specific(B)))))
1979 return Op0;
1980
1981 // (A & B) | (~A ^ B) -> (~A ^ B)
1982 // (B & A) | (~A ^ B) -> (~A ^ B)
1983 // (A & B) | (B ^ ~A) -> (B ^ ~A)
1984 // (B & A) | (B ^ ~A) -> (B ^ ~A)
1985 if (match(Op0, m_And(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
1986 (match(Op1, m_c_Xor(m_Specific(A), m_Not(m_Specific(B)))) ||
1987 match(Op1, m_c_Xor(m_Not(m_Specific(A)), m_Specific(B)))))
1988 return Op1;
1989
1990 // (~A ^ B) | (A & B) -> (~A ^ B)
1991 // (~A ^ B) | (B & A) -> (~A ^ B)
1992 // (B ^ ~A) | (A & B) -> (B ^ ~A)
1993 // (B ^ ~A) | (B & A) -> (B ^ ~A)
1994 if (match(Op1, m_And(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
1995 (match(Op0, m_c_Xor(m_Specific(A), m_Not(m_Specific(B)))) ||
1996 match(Op0, m_c_Xor(m_Not(m_Specific(A)), m_Specific(B)))))
1997 return Op0;
1998
1999 if (Value *V = simplifyAndOrOfCmps(Q, Op0, Op1, false))
2000 return V;
2001
2002 // Try some generic simplifications for associative operations.
2003 if (Value *V = SimplifyAssociativeBinOp(Instruction::Or, Op0, Op1, Q,
2004 MaxRecurse))
2005 return V;
2006
2007 // Or distributes over And. Try some generic simplifications based on this.
2008 if (Value *V = ExpandBinOp(Instruction::Or, Op0, Op1, Instruction::And, Q,
2009 MaxRecurse))
2010 return V;
2011
2012 // If the operation is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
2013 // operating on either branch of the select always yields the same value.
2014 if (isa<SelectInst>(Op0) || isa<SelectInst>(Op1))
2015 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverSelect(Instruction::Or, Op0, Op1, Q,
2016 MaxRecurse))
2017 return V;
2018
2019 // (A & C1)|(B & C2)
2020 const APInt *C1, *C2;
2021 if (match(Op0, m_And(m_Value(A), m_APInt(C1))) &&
2022 match(Op1, m_And(m_Value(B), m_APInt(C2)))) {
2023 if (*C1 == ~*C2) {
2024 // (A & C1)|(B & C2)
2025 // If we have: ((V + N) & C1) | (V & C2)
2026 // .. and C2 = ~C1 and C2 is 0+1+ and (N & C2) == 0
2027 // replace with V+N.
2028 Value *N;
2029 if (C2->isMask() && // C2 == 0+1+
2030 match(A, m_c_Add(m_Specific(B), m_Value(N)))) {
2031 // Add commutes, try both ways.
2032 if (MaskedValueIsZero(N, *C2, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT))
2033 return A;
2034 }
2035 // Or commutes, try both ways.
2036 if (C1->isMask() &&
2037 match(B, m_c_Add(m_Specific(A), m_Value(N)))) {
2038 // Add commutes, try both ways.
2039 if (MaskedValueIsZero(N, *C1, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT))
2040 return B;
2041 }
2042 }
2043 }
2044
2045 // If the operation is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
2046 // operating on all incoming values of the phi always yields the same value.
2047 if (isa<PHINode>(Op0) || isa<PHINode>(Op1))
2048 if (Value *V = ThreadBinOpOverPHI(Instruction::Or, Op0, Op1, Q, MaxRecurse))
2049 return V;
2050
2051 return nullptr;
2052}

2054Value *llvm::SimplifyOrInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
2055 return ::SimplifyOrInst(Op0, Op1, Q, RecursionLimit);
2056}

2058/// Given operands for a Xor, see if we can fold the result.
2059/// If not, this returns null.
2060static Value *SimplifyXorInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
2061 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
2062 if (Constant *C = foldOrCommuteConstant(Instruction::Xor, Op0, Op1, Q))
2063 return C;
2064
2065 // A ^ undef -> undef
2066 if (match(Op1, m_Undef()))
2067 return Op1;
2068
2069 // A ^ 0 = A
2070 if (match(Op1, m_Zero()))
2071 return Op0;
2072
2073 // A ^ A = 0
2074 if (Op0 == Op1)
2075 return Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
2076
2077 // A ^ ~A = ~A ^ A = -1
2078 if (match(Op0, m_Not(m_Specific(Op1))) ||
2079 match(Op1, m_Not(m_Specific(Op0))))
2080 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
2081
2082 // Try some generic simplifications for associative operations.
2083 if (Value *V = SimplifyAssociativeBinOp(Instruction::Xor, Op0, Op1, Q,
2084 MaxRecurse))
2085 return V;
2086
2087 // Threading Xor over selects and phi nodes is pointless, so don't bother.
2088 // Threading over the select in "A ^ select(cond, B, C)" means evaluating
2089 // "A^B" and "A^C" and seeing if they are equal; but they are equal if and
2090 // only if B and C are equal. If B and C are equal then (since we assume
2091 // that operands have already been simplified) "select(cond, B, C)" should
2092 // have been simplified to the common value of B and C already. Analysing
2093 // "A^B" and "A^C" thus gains nothing, but costs compile time. Similarly
2094 // for threading over phi nodes.
2095
2096 return nullptr;
2097}

2099Value *llvm::SimplifyXorInst(Value *Op0, Value *Op1, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
2100 return ::SimplifyXorInst(Op0, Op1, Q, RecursionLimit);
2101}
