2108/// Rummage around inside V looking for something equivalent to the comparison
2109/// "LHS Pred RHS". Return such a value if found, otherwise return null.
2110/// Helper function for analyzing max/min idioms.
2111static Value *ExtractEquivalentCondition(Value *V, CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
2112 Value *LHS, Value *RHS) {
2113 SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V);
2114 if (!SI)
2115 return nullptr;
2116 CmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(SI->getCondition());
2117 if (!Cmp)
2118 return nullptr;
2119 Value *CmpLHS = Cmp->getOperand(0), *CmpRHS = Cmp->getOperand(1);
2120 if (Pred == Cmp->getPredicate() && LHS == CmpLHS && RHS == CmpRHS)
2121 return Cmp;
2122 if (Pred == CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Cmp->getPredicate()) &&
2123 LHS == CmpRHS && RHS == CmpLHS)
2124 return Cmp;
2125 return nullptr;
2126}
2127
2128// A significant optimization not implemented here is assuming that alloca
2129// addresses are not equal to incoming argument values. They don't *alias*,
2130// as we say, but that doesn't mean they aren't equal, so we take a
2131// conservative approach.
2132//
2133// This is inspired in part by C++11 5.10p1:
2134// "Two pointers of the same type compare equal if and only if they are both
2135// null, both point to the same function, or both represent the same
2136// address."
2137//
2138// This is pretty permissive.
2139//
2140// It's also partly due to C11 6.5.9p6:
2141// "Two pointers compare equal if and only if both are null pointers, both are
2142// pointers to the same object (including a pointer to an object and a
2143// subobject at its beginning) or function, both are pointers to one past the
2144// last element of the same array object, or one is a pointer to one past the
2145// end of one array object and the other is a pointer to the start of a
2146// different array object that happens to immediately follow the first array
2147// object in the address space.)
2148//
2149// C11's version is more restrictive, however there's no reason why an argument
2150// couldn't be a one-past-the-end value for a stack object in the caller and be
2151// equal to the beginning of a stack object in the callee.
2152//
2153// If the C and C++ standards are ever made sufficiently restrictive in this
2154// area, it may be possible to update LLVM's semantics accordingly and reinstate
2155// this optimization.
2156static Constant *
2157computePointerICmp(const DataLayout &DL, const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2158 const DominatorTree *DT, CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
2159 AssumptionCache *AC, const Instruction *CxtI,
2160 const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ, Value *LHS, Value *RHS) {
2161 // First, skip past any trivial no-ops.
2162 LHS = LHS->stripPointerCasts();
2163 RHS = RHS->stripPointerCasts();
2164
2165 // A non-null pointer is not equal to a null pointer.
2166 if (llvm::isKnownNonZero(LHS, DL, 0, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
2167 IIQ.UseInstrInfo) &&
2168 isa<ConstantPointerNull>(RHS) &&
2169 (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE))
2170 return ConstantInt::get(GetCompareTy(LHS),
2171 !CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred));
2172
2173 // We can only fold certain predicates on pointer comparisons.
2174 switch (Pred) {
2175 default:
2176 return nullptr;
2177
2178 // Equality comaprisons are easy to fold.
2179 case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2180 case CmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2181 break;
2182
2183 // We can only handle unsigned relational comparisons because 'inbounds' on
2184 // a GEP only protects against unsigned wrapping.
2185 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
2186 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
2187 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
2188 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
2189 // However, we have to switch them to their signed variants to handle
2190 // negative indices from the base pointer.
2191 Pred = ICmpInst::getSignedPredicate(Pred);
2192 break;
2193 }
2194
2195 // Strip off any constant offsets so that we can reason about them.
2196 // It's tempting to use getUnderlyingObject or even just stripInBoundsOffsets
2197 // here and compare base addresses like AliasAnalysis does, however there are
2198 // numerous hazards. AliasAnalysis and its utilities rely on special rules
2199 // governing loads and stores which don't apply to icmps. Also, AliasAnalysis
2200 // doesn't need to guarantee pointer inequality when it says NoAlias.
2201 Constant *LHSOffset = stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(DL, LHS);
2202 Constant *RHSOffset = stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(DL, RHS);
2203
2204 // If LHS and RHS are related via constant offsets to the same base
2205 // value, we can replace it with an icmp which just compares the offsets.
2206 if (LHS == RHS)
2207 return ConstantExpr::getICmp(Pred, LHSOffset, RHSOffset);
2208
2209 // Various optimizations for (in)equality comparisons.
2210 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE) {
2211 // Different non-empty allocations that exist at the same time have
2212 // different addresses (if the program can tell). Global variables always
2213 // exist, so they always exist during the lifetime of each other and all
2214 // allocas. Two different allocas usually have different addresses...
2215 //
2216 // However, if there's an @llvm.stackrestore dynamically in between two
2217 // allocas, they may have the same address. It's tempting to reduce the
2218 // scope of the problem by only looking at *static* allocas here. That would
2219 // cover the majority of allocas while significantly reducing the likelihood
2220 // of having an @llvm.stackrestore pop up in the middle. However, it's not
2221 // actually impossible for an @llvm.stackrestore to pop up in the middle of
2222 // an entry block. Also, if we have a block that's not attached to a
2223 // function, we can't tell if it's "static" under the current definition.
2224 // Theoretically, this problem could be fixed by creating a new kind of
2225 // instruction kind specifically for static allocas. Such a new instruction
2226 // could be required to be at the top of the entry block, thus preventing it
2227 // from being subject to a @llvm.stackrestore. Instcombine could even
2228 // convert regular allocas into these special allocas. It'd be nifty.
2229 // However, until then, this problem remains open.
2230 //
2231 // So, we'll assume that two non-empty allocas have different addresses
2232 // for now.
2233 //
2234 // With all that, if the offsets are within the bounds of their allocations
2235 // (and not one-past-the-end! so we can't use inbounds!), and their
2236 // allocations aren't the same, the pointers are not equal.
2237 //
2238 // Note that it's not necessary to check for LHS being a global variable
2239 // address, due to canonicalization and constant folding.
2240 if (isa<AllocaInst>(LHS) &&
2241 (isa<AllocaInst>(RHS) || isa<GlobalVariable>(RHS))) {
2242 ConstantInt *LHSOffsetCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(LHSOffset);
2243 ConstantInt *RHSOffsetCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(RHSOffset);
2244 uint64_t LHSSize, RHSSize;
2245 ObjectSizeOpts Opts;
2246 Opts.NullIsUnknownSize =
2247 NullPointerIsDefined(cast<AllocaInst>(LHS)->getFunction());
2248 if (LHSOffsetCI && RHSOffsetCI &&
2249 getObjectSize(LHS, LHSSize, DL, TLI, Opts) &&
2250 getObjectSize(RHS, RHSSize, DL, TLI, Opts)) {
2251 const APInt &LHSOffsetValue = LHSOffsetCI->getValue();
2252 const APInt &RHSOffsetValue = RHSOffsetCI->getValue();
2253 if (!LHSOffsetValue.isNegative() &&
2254 !RHSOffsetValue.isNegative() &&
2255 LHSOffsetValue.ult(LHSSize) &&
2256 RHSOffsetValue.ult(RHSSize)) {
2257 return ConstantInt::get(GetCompareTy(LHS),
2258 !CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred));
2259 }
2260 }
2261
2262 // Repeat the above check but this time without depending on DataLayout
2263 // or being able to compute a precise size.
2264 if (!cast<PointerType>(LHS->getType())->isEmptyTy() &&
2265 !cast<PointerType>(RHS->getType())->isEmptyTy() &&
2266 LHSOffset->isNullValue() &&
2267 RHSOffset->isNullValue())
2268 return ConstantInt::get(GetCompareTy(LHS),
2269 !CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred));
2270 }
2271
2272 // Even if an non-inbounds GEP occurs along the path we can still optimize
2273 // equality comparisons concerning the result. We avoid walking the whole
2274 // chain again by starting where the last calls to
2275 // stripAndComputeConstantOffsets left off and accumulate the offsets.
2276 Constant *LHSNoBound = stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(DL, LHS, true);
2277 Constant *RHSNoBound = stripAndComputeConstantOffsets(DL, RHS, true);
2278 if (LHS == RHS)
2279 return ConstantExpr::getICmp(Pred,
2280 ConstantExpr::getAdd(LHSOffset, LHSNoBound),
2281 ConstantExpr::getAdd(RHSOffset, RHSNoBound));
2282
2283 // If one side of the equality comparison must come from a noalias call
2284 // (meaning a system memory allocation function), and the other side must
2285 // come from a pointer that cannot overlap with dynamically-allocated
2286 // memory within the lifetime of the current function (allocas, byval
2287 // arguments, globals), then determine the comparison result here.
2288 SmallVector<const Value *, 8> LHSUObjs, RHSUObjs;
2289 GetUnderlyingObjects(LHS, LHSUObjs, DL);
2290 GetUnderlyingObjects(RHS, RHSUObjs, DL);
2291
2292 // Is the set of underlying objects all noalias calls?
2293 auto IsNAC = [](ArrayRef<const Value *> Objects) {
2294 return all_of(Objects, isNoAliasCall);
2295 };
2296
2297 // Is the set of underlying objects all things which must be disjoint from
2298 // noalias calls. For allocas, we consider only static ones (dynamic
2299 // allocas might be transformed into calls to malloc not simultaneously
2300 // live with the compared-to allocation). For globals, we exclude symbols
2301 // that might be resolve lazily to symbols in another dynamically-loaded
2302 // library (and, thus, could be malloc'ed by the implementation).
2303 auto IsAllocDisjoint = [](ArrayRef<const Value *> Objects) {
2304 return all_of(Objects, [](const Value *V) {
2305 if (const AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(V))
2306 return AI->getParent() && AI->getFunction() && AI->isStaticAlloca();
2307 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(V))
2308 return (GV->hasLocalLinkage() || GV->hasHiddenVisibility() ||
2309 GV->hasProtectedVisibility() || GV->hasGlobalUnnamedAddr()) &&
2310 !GV->isThreadLocal();
2311 if (const Argument *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(V))
2312 return A->hasByValAttr();
2313 return false;
2314 });
2315 };
2316
2317 if ((IsNAC(LHSUObjs) && IsAllocDisjoint(RHSUObjs)) ||
2318 (IsNAC(RHSUObjs) && IsAllocDisjoint(LHSUObjs)))
2319 return ConstantInt::get(GetCompareTy(LHS),
2320 !CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred));
2321
2322 // Fold comparisons for non-escaping pointer even if the allocation call
2323 // cannot be elided. We cannot fold malloc comparison to null. Also, the
2324 // dynamic allocation call could be either of the operands.
2325 Value *MI = nullptr;
2326 if (isAllocLikeFn(LHS, TLI) &&
2327 llvm::isKnownNonZero(RHS, DL, 0, nullptr, CxtI, DT))
2328 MI = LHS;
2329 else if (isAllocLikeFn(RHS, TLI) &&
2330 llvm::isKnownNonZero(LHS, DL, 0, nullptr, CxtI, DT))
2331 MI = RHS;
2332 // FIXME: We should also fold the compare when the pointer escapes, but the
2333 // compare dominates the pointer escape
2334 if (MI && !PointerMayBeCaptured(MI, true, true))
2335 return ConstantInt::get(GetCompareTy(LHS),
2336 CmpInst::isFalseWhenEqual(Pred));
2337 }
2338
2339 // Otherwise, fail.
2340 return nullptr;
2341}
2342
2343/// Fold an icmp when its operands have i1 scalar type.
2344static Value *simplifyICmpOfBools(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
2345 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
2346 Type *ITy = GetCompareTy(LHS); // The return type.
2347 Type *OpTy = LHS->getType(); // The operand type.
2348 if (!OpTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1))
2349 return nullptr;
2350
2351 // A boolean compared to true/false can be simplified in 14 out of the 20
2352 // (10 predicates * 2 constants) possible combinations. Cases not handled here
2353 // require a 'not' of the LHS, so those must be transformed in InstCombine.
2354 if (match(RHS, m_Zero())) {
2355 switch (Pred) {
2356 case CmpInst::ICMP_NE: // X != 0 -> X
2357 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: // X >u 0 -> X
2358 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: // X <s 0 -> X
2359 return LHS;
2360
2361 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: // X <u 0 -> false
2362 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: // X >s 0 -> false
2363 return getFalse(ITy);
2364
2365 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE: // X >=u 0 -> true
2366 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: // X <=s 0 -> true
2367 return getTrue(ITy);
2368
2369 default: break;
2370 }
2371 } else if (match(RHS, m_One())) {
2372 switch (Pred) {
2373 case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ: // X == 1 -> X
2374 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE: // X >=u 1 -> X
2375 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: // X <=s -1 -> X
2376 return LHS;
2377
2378 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: // X >u 1 -> false
2379 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: // X <s -1 -> false
2380 return getFalse(ITy);
2381
2382 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: // X <=u 1 -> true
2383 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE: // X >=s -1 -> true
2384 return getTrue(ITy);
2385
2386 default: break;
2387 }
2388 }
2389
2390 switch (Pred) {
2391 default:
2392 break;
2393 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
2394 if (isImpliedCondition(RHS, LHS, Q.DL).getValueOr(false))
2395 return getTrue(ITy);
2396 break;
2397 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
2398 /// For signed comparison, the values for an i1 are 0 and -1
2399 /// respectively. This maps into a truth table of:
2400 /// LHS | RHS | LHS >=s RHS | LHS implies RHS
2401 /// 0 | 0 | 1 (0 >= 0) | 1
2402 /// 0 | 1 | 1 (0 >= -1) | 1
2403 /// 1 | 0 | 0 (-1 >= 0) | 0
2404 /// 1 | 1 | 1 (-1 >= -1) | 1
2405 if (isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS, Q.DL).getValueOr(false))
2406 return getTrue(ITy);
2407 break;
2408 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
2409 if (isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS, Q.DL).getValueOr(false))
2410 return getTrue(ITy);
2411 break;
2412 }
2413
2414 return nullptr;
2415}
2416
2417/// Try hard to fold icmp with zero RHS because this is a common case.
2418static Value *simplifyICmpWithZero(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
2419 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
2420 if (!match(RHS, m_Zero()))
2421 return nullptr;
2422
2423 Type *ITy = GetCompareTy(LHS); // The return type.
2424 switch (Pred) {
2425 default:
2426 llvm_unreachable("Unknown ICmp predicate!");
2427 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
2428 return getFalse(ITy);
2429 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
2430 return getTrue(ITy);
2431 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2432 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
2433 if (isKnownNonZero(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT, Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo))
2434 return getFalse(ITy);
2435 break;
2436 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2437 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
2438 if (isKnownNonZero(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT, Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo))
2439 return getTrue(ITy);
2440 break;
2441 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT: {
2442 KnownBits LHSKnown = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2443 if (LHSKnown.isNegative())
2444 return getTrue(ITy);
2445 if (LHSKnown.isNonNegative())
2446 return getFalse(ITy);
2447 break;
2448 }
2449 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
2450 KnownBits LHSKnown = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2451 if (LHSKnown.isNegative())
2452 return getTrue(ITy);
2453 if (LHSKnown.isNonNegative() &&
2454 isKnownNonZero(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT))
2455 return getFalse(ITy);
2456 break;
2457 }
2458 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: {
2459 KnownBits LHSKnown = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2460 if (LHSKnown.isNegative())
2461 return getFalse(ITy);
2462 if (LHSKnown.isNonNegative())
2463 return getTrue(ITy);
2464 break;
2465 }
2466 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT: {
2467 KnownBits LHSKnown = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2468 if (LHSKnown.isNegative())
2469 return getFalse(ITy);
2470 if (LHSKnown.isNonNegative() &&
2471 isKnownNonZero(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT))
2472 return getTrue(ITy);
2473 break;
2474 }
2475 }
2476
2477 return nullptr;
2478}
2479
2480static Value *simplifyICmpWithConstant(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
2481 Value *RHS, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
2482 Type *ITy = GetCompareTy(RHS); // The return type.
2483
2484 Value *X;
2485 // Sign-bit checks can be optimized to true/false after unsigned
2486 // floating-point casts:
2487 // icmp slt (bitcast (uitofp X)), 0 --> false
2488 // icmp sgt (bitcast (uitofp X)), -1 --> true
2489 if (match(LHS, m_BitCast(m_UIToFP(m_Value(X))))) {
2490 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(RHS, m_Zero()))
2491 return ConstantInt::getFalse(ITy);
2492 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(RHS, m_AllOnes()))
2493 return ConstantInt::getTrue(ITy);
2494 }
2495
2496 const APInt *C;
2497 if (!match(RHS, m_APInt(C)))
2498 return nullptr;
2499
2500 // Rule out tautological comparisons (eg., ult 0 or uge 0).
2501 ConstantRange RHS_CR = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(Pred, *C);
2502 if (RHS_CR.isEmptySet())
2503 return ConstantInt::getFalse(ITy);
2504 if (RHS_CR.isFullSet())
2505 return ConstantInt::getTrue(ITy);
2506
2507 ConstantRange LHS_CR = computeConstantRange(LHS, IIQ.UseInstrInfo);
2508 if (!LHS_CR.isFullSet()) {
2509 if (RHS_CR.contains(LHS_CR))
2510 return ConstantInt::getTrue(ITy);
2511 if (RHS_CR.inverse().contains(LHS_CR))
2512 return ConstantInt::getFalse(ITy);
2513 }
2514
2515 return nullptr;
2516}

2518/// TODO: A large part of this logic is duplicated in InstCombine's
2519/// foldICmpBinOp(). We should be able to share that and avoid the code
2520/// duplication.
2521static Value *simplifyICmpWithBinOp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
2522 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
2523 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
2524 Type *ITy = GetCompareTy(LHS); // The return type.
2525
2526 BinaryOperator *LBO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(LHS);
2527 BinaryOperator *RBO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(RHS);
2528 if (MaxRecurse && (LBO || RBO)) {
2529 // Analyze the case when either LHS or RHS is an add instruction.
2530 Value *A = nullptr, *B = nullptr, *C = nullptr, *D = nullptr;
2531 // LHS = A + B (or A and B are null); RHS = C + D (or C and D are null).
2532 bool NoLHSWrapProblem = false, NoRHSWrapProblem = false;
2533 if (LBO && LBO->getOpcode() == Instruction::Add) {
2534 A = LBO->getOperand(0);
2535 B = LBO->getOperand(1);
2536 NoLHSWrapProblem =
2537 ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) ||
2538 (CmpInst::isUnsigned(Pred) &&
2539 Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(LBO))) ||
2540 (CmpInst::isSigned(Pred) &&
2541 Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(LBO)));
2542 }
2543 if (RBO && RBO->getOpcode() == Instruction::Add) {
2544 C = RBO->getOperand(0);
2545 D = RBO->getOperand(1);
2546 NoRHSWrapProblem =
2547 ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) ||
2548 (CmpInst::isUnsigned(Pred) &&
2549 Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(RBO))) ||
2550 (CmpInst::isSigned(Pred) &&
2551 Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(RBO)));
2552 }
2553
2554 // icmp (X+Y), X -> icmp Y, 0 for equalities or if there is no overflow.
2555 if ((A == RHS || B == RHS) && NoLHSWrapProblem)
2556 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, A == RHS ? B : A,
2557 Constant::getNullValue(RHS->getType()), Q,
2558 MaxRecurse - 1))
2559 return V;
2560
2561 // icmp X, (X+Y) -> icmp 0, Y for equalities or if there is no overflow.
2562 if ((C == LHS || D == LHS) && NoRHSWrapProblem)
2563 if (Value *V =
2564 SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, Constant::getNullValue(LHS->getType()),
2565 C == LHS ? D : C, Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2566 return V;
2567
2568 // icmp (X+Y), (X+Z) -> icmp Y,Z for equalities or if there is no overflow.
2569 if (A && C && (A == C || A == D || B == C || B == D) && NoLHSWrapProblem &&
2570 NoRHSWrapProblem) {
2571 // Determine Y and Z in the form icmp (X+Y), (X+Z).
2572 Value *Y, *Z;
2573 if (A == C) {
2574 // C + B == C + D -> B == D
2575 Y = B;
2576 Z = D;
2577 } else if (A == D) {
2578 // D + B == C + D -> B == C
2579 Y = B;
2580 Z = C;
2581 } else if (B == C) {
2582 // A + C == C + D -> A == D
2583 Y = A;
2584 Z = D;
2585 } else {
2586 assert(B == D);
2587 // A + D == C + D -> A == C
2588 Y = A;
2589 Z = C;
2590 }
2591 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, Y, Z, Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2592 return V;
2593 }
2594 }
2595
2596 {
2597 Value *Y = nullptr;
2598 // icmp pred (or X, Y), X
2599 if (LBO && match(LBO, m_c_Or(m_Value(Y), m_Specific(RHS)))) {
2600 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
2601 return getFalse(ITy);
2602 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
2603 return getTrue(ITy);
2604
2605 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE) {
2606 KnownBits RHSKnown = computeKnownBits(RHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2607 KnownBits YKnown = computeKnownBits(Y, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2608 if (RHSKnown.isNonNegative() && YKnown.isNegative())
2609 return Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT ? getTrue(ITy) : getFalse(ITy);
2610 if (RHSKnown.isNegative() || YKnown.isNonNegative())
2611 return Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT ? getFalse(ITy) : getTrue(ITy);
2612 }
2613 }
2614 // icmp pred X, (or X, Y)
2615 if (RBO && match(RBO, m_c_Or(m_Value(Y), m_Specific(LHS)))) {
2616 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
2617 return getTrue(ITy);
2618 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
2619 return getFalse(ITy);
2620
2621 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE) {
2622 KnownBits LHSKnown = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2623 KnownBits YKnown = computeKnownBits(Y, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2624 if (LHSKnown.isNonNegative() && YKnown.isNegative())
2625 return Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? getTrue(ITy) : getFalse(ITy);
2626 if (LHSKnown.isNegative() || YKnown.isNonNegative())
2627 return Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? getFalse(ITy) : getTrue(ITy);
2628 }
2629 }
2630 }
2631
2632 // icmp pred (and X, Y), X
2633 if (LBO && match(LBO, m_c_And(m_Value(), m_Specific(RHS)))) {
2634 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
2635 return getFalse(ITy);
2636 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
2637 return getTrue(ITy);
2638 }
2639 // icmp pred X, (and X, Y)
2640 if (RBO && match(RBO, m_c_And(m_Value(), m_Specific(LHS)))) {
2641 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
2642 return getTrue(ITy);
2643 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
2644 return getFalse(ITy);
2645 }
2646
2647 // 0 - (zext X) pred C
2648 if (!CmpInst::isUnsigned(Pred) && match(LHS, m_Neg(m_ZExt(m_Value())))) {
2649 if (ConstantInt *RHSC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
2650 if (RHSC->getValue().isStrictlyPositive()) {
2651 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
2652 return ConstantInt::getTrue(RHSC->getContext());
2653 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
2654 return ConstantInt::getFalse(RHSC->getContext());
2655 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
2656 return ConstantInt::getFalse(RHSC->getContext());
2657 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
2658 return ConstantInt::getTrue(RHSC->getContext());
2659 }
2660 if (RHSC->getValue().isNonNegative()) {
2661 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
2662 return ConstantInt::getTrue(RHSC->getContext());
2663 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
2664 return ConstantInt::getFalse(RHSC->getContext());
2665 }
2666 }
2667 }
2668
2669 // icmp pred (urem X, Y), Y
2670 if (LBO && match(LBO, m_URem(m_Value(), m_Specific(RHS)))) {
2671 switch (Pred) {
2672 default:
2673 break;
2674 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
2675 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: {
2676 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(RHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2677 if (!Known.isNonNegative())
2678 break;
2679 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2680 }
2681 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2682 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
2683 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
2684 return getFalse(ITy);
2685 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
2686 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
2687 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(RHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2688 if (!Known.isNonNegative())
2689 break;
2690 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2691 }
2692 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2693 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
2694 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
2695 return getTrue(ITy);
2696 }
2697 }
2698
2699 // icmp pred X, (urem Y, X)
2700 if (RBO && match(RBO, m_URem(m_Value(), m_Specific(LHS)))) {
2701 switch (Pred) {
2702 default:
2703 break;
2704 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
2705 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: {
2706 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2707 if (!Known.isNonNegative())
2708 break;
2709 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2710 }
2711 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2712 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
2713 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
2714 return getTrue(ITy);
2715 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
2716 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
2717 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(LHS, Q.DL, 0, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT);
2718 if (!Known.isNonNegative())
2719 break;
2720 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2721 }
2722 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2723 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
2724 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
2725 return getFalse(ITy);
2726 }
2727 }
2728
2729 // x >> y <=u x
2730 // x udiv y <=u x.
2731 if (LBO && (match(LBO, m_LShr(m_Specific(RHS), m_Value())) ||
2732 match(LBO, m_UDiv(m_Specific(RHS), m_Value())))) {
2733 // icmp pred (X op Y), X
2734 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
2735 return getFalse(ITy);
2736 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
2737 return getTrue(ITy);
2738 }
2739
2740 // x >=u x >> y
2741 // x >=u x udiv y.
2742 if (RBO && (match(RBO, m_LShr(m_Specific(LHS), m_Value())) ||
2743 match(RBO, m_UDiv(m_Specific(LHS), m_Value())))) {
2744 // icmp pred X, (X op Y)
2745 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
2746 return getFalse(ITy);
2747 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
2748 return getTrue(ITy);
2749 }
2750
2751 // handle:
2752 // CI2 << X == CI
2753 // CI2 << X != CI
2754 //
2755 // where CI2 is a power of 2 and CI isn't
2756 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
2757 const APInt *CI2Val, *CIVal = &CI->getValue();
2758 if (LBO && match(LBO, m_Shl(m_APInt(CI2Val), m_Value())) &&
2759 CI2Val->isPowerOf2()) {
2760 if (!CIVal->isPowerOf2()) {
2761 // CI2 << X can equal zero in some circumstances,
2762 // this simplification is unsafe if CI is zero.
2763 //
2764 // We know it is safe if:
2765 // - The shift is nsw, we can't shift out the one bit.
2766 // - The shift is nuw, we can't shift out the one bit.
2767 // - CI2 is one
2768 // - CI isn't zero
2769 if (Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(LBO)) ||
2770 Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(LBO)) ||
2771 CI2Val->isOneValue() || !CI->isZero()) {
2772 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
2773 return ConstantInt::getFalse(RHS->getContext());
2774 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
2775 return ConstantInt::getTrue(RHS->getContext());
2776 }
2777 }
2778 if (CIVal->isSignMask() && CI2Val->isOneValue()) {
2779 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
2780 return ConstantInt::getFalse(RHS->getContext());
2781 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
2782 return ConstantInt::getTrue(RHS->getContext());
2783 }
2784 }
2785 }
2786
2787 if (MaxRecurse && LBO && RBO && LBO->getOpcode() == RBO->getOpcode() &&
2788 LBO->getOperand(1) == RBO->getOperand(1)) {
2789 switch (LBO->getOpcode()) {
2790 default:
2791 break;
2792 case Instruction::UDiv:
2793 case Instruction::LShr:
2794 if (ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred) || !Q.IIQ.isExact(LBO) ||
2795 !Q.IIQ.isExact(RBO))
2796 break;
2797 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, LBO->getOperand(0),
2798 RBO->getOperand(0), Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2799 return V;
2800 break;
2801 case Instruction::SDiv:
2802 if (!ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) || !Q.IIQ.isExact(LBO) ||
2803 !Q.IIQ.isExact(RBO))
2804 break;
2805 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, LBO->getOperand(0),
2806 RBO->getOperand(0), Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2807 return V;
2808 break;
2809 case Instruction::AShr:
2810 if (!Q.IIQ.isExact(LBO) || !Q.IIQ.isExact(RBO))
2811 break;
2812 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, LBO->getOperand(0),
2813 RBO->getOperand(0), Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2814 return V;
2815 break;
2816 case Instruction::Shl: {
2817 bool NUW = Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(LBO) && Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(RBO);
2818 bool NSW = Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(LBO) && Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(RBO);
2819 if (!NUW && !NSW)
2820 break;
2821 if (!NSW && ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred))
2822 break;
2823 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, LBO->getOperand(0),
2824 RBO->getOperand(0), Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2825 return V;
2826 break;
2827 }
2828 }
2829 }
2830 return nullptr;
2831}
2832
2833/// Simplify integer comparisons where at least one operand of the compare
2834/// matches an integer min/max idiom.
2835static Value *simplifyICmpWithMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *LHS,
2836 Value *RHS, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
2837 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
2838 Type *ITy = GetCompareTy(LHS); // The return type.
2839 Value *A, *B;
2840 CmpInst::Predicate P = CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE;
2841 CmpInst::Predicate EqP; // Chosen so that "A == max/min(A,B)" iff "A EqP B".
2842
2843 // Signed variants on "max(a,b)>=a -> true".
2844 if (match(LHS, m_SMax(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) && (A == RHS || B == RHS)) {
2845 if (A != RHS)
2846 std::swap(A, B); // smax(A, B) pred A.
2847 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_SGE; // "A == smax(A, B)" iff "A sge B".
2848 // We analyze this as smax(A, B) pred A.
2849 P = Pred;
2850 } else if (match(RHS, m_SMax(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2851 (A == LHS || B == LHS)) {
2852 if (A != LHS)
2853 std::swap(A, B); // A pred smax(A, B).
2854 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_SGE; // "A == smax(A, B)" iff "A sge B".
2855 // We analyze this as smax(A, B) swapped-pred A.
2856 P = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
2857 } else if (match(LHS, m_SMin(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2858 (A == RHS || B == RHS)) {
2859 if (A != RHS)
2860 std::swap(A, B); // smin(A, B) pred A.
2861 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_SLE; // "A == smin(A, B)" iff "A sle B".
2862 // We analyze this as smax(-A, -B) swapped-pred -A.
2863 // Note that we do not need to actually form -A or -B thanks to EqP.
2864 P = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
2865 } else if (match(RHS, m_SMin(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2866 (A == LHS || B == LHS)) {
2867 if (A != LHS)
2868 std::swap(A, B); // A pred smin(A, B).
2869 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_SLE; // "A == smin(A, B)" iff "A sle B".
2870 // We analyze this as smax(-A, -B) pred -A.
2871 // Note that we do not need to actually form -A or -B thanks to EqP.
2872 P = Pred;
2873 }
2874 if (P != CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE) {
2875 // Cases correspond to "max(A, B) p A".
2876 switch (P) {
2877 default:
2878 break;
2879 case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2880 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
2881 // Equivalent to "A EqP B". This may be the same as the condition tested
2882 // in the max/min; if so, we can just return that.
2883 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(LHS, EqP, A, B))
2884 return V;
2885 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(RHS, EqP, A, B))
2886 return V;
2887 // Otherwise, see if "A EqP B" simplifies.
2888 if (MaxRecurse)
2889 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(EqP, A, B, Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2890 return V;
2891 break;
2892 case CmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2893 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: {
2894 CmpInst::Predicate InvEqP = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(EqP);
2895 // Equivalent to "A InvEqP B". This may be the same as the condition
2896 // tested in the max/min; if so, we can just return that.
2897 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(LHS, InvEqP, A, B))
2898 return V;
2899 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(RHS, InvEqP, A, B))
2900 return V;
2901 // Otherwise, see if "A InvEqP B" simplifies.
2902 if (MaxRecurse)
2903 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(InvEqP, A, B, Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2904 return V;
2905 break;
2906 }
2907 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
2908 // Always true.
2909 return getTrue(ITy);
2910 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
2911 // Always false.
2912 return getFalse(ITy);
2913 }
2914 }
2915
2916 // Unsigned variants on "max(a,b)>=a -> true".
2917 P = CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE;
2918 if (match(LHS, m_UMax(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) && (A == RHS || B == RHS)) {
2919 if (A != RHS)
2920 std::swap(A, B); // umax(A, B) pred A.
2921 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_UGE; // "A == umax(A, B)" iff "A uge B".
2922 // We analyze this as umax(A, B) pred A.
2923 P = Pred;
2924 } else if (match(RHS, m_UMax(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2925 (A == LHS || B == LHS)) {
2926 if (A != LHS)
2927 std::swap(A, B); // A pred umax(A, B).
2928 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_UGE; // "A == umax(A, B)" iff "A uge B".
2929 // We analyze this as umax(A, B) swapped-pred A.
2930 P = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
2931 } else if (match(LHS, m_UMin(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2932 (A == RHS || B == RHS)) {
2933 if (A != RHS)
2934 std::swap(A, B); // umin(A, B) pred A.
2935 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_ULE; // "A == umin(A, B)" iff "A ule B".
2936 // We analyze this as umax(-A, -B) swapped-pred -A.
2937 // Note that we do not need to actually form -A or -B thanks to EqP.
2938 P = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
2939 } else if (match(RHS, m_UMin(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2940 (A == LHS || B == LHS)) {
2941 if (A != LHS)
2942 std::swap(A, B); // A pred umin(A, B).
2943 EqP = CmpInst::ICMP_ULE; // "A == umin(A, B)" iff "A ule B".
2944 // We analyze this as umax(-A, -B) pred -A.
2945 // Note that we do not need to actually form -A or -B thanks to EqP.
2946 P = Pred;
2947 }
2948 if (P != CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE) {
2949 // Cases correspond to "max(A, B) p A".
2950 switch (P) {
2951 default:
2952 break;
2953 case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2954 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
2955 // Equivalent to "A EqP B". This may be the same as the condition tested
2956 // in the max/min; if so, we can just return that.
2957 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(LHS, EqP, A, B))
2958 return V;
2959 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(RHS, EqP, A, B))
2960 return V;
2961 // Otherwise, see if "A EqP B" simplifies.
2962 if (MaxRecurse)
2963 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(EqP, A, B, Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2964 return V;
2965 break;
2966 case CmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2967 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: {
2968 CmpInst::Predicate InvEqP = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(EqP);
2969 // Equivalent to "A InvEqP B". This may be the same as the condition
2970 // tested in the max/min; if so, we can just return that.
2971 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(LHS, InvEqP, A, B))
2972 return V;
2973 if (Value *V = ExtractEquivalentCondition(RHS, InvEqP, A, B))
2974 return V;
2975 // Otherwise, see if "A InvEqP B" simplifies.
2976 if (MaxRecurse)
2977 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(InvEqP, A, B, Q, MaxRecurse - 1))
2978 return V;
2979 break;
2980 }
2981 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
2982 // Always true.
2983 return getTrue(ITy);
2984 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
2985 // Always false.
2986 return getFalse(ITy);
2987 }
2988 }
2989
2990 // Variants on "max(x,y) >= min(x,z)".
2991 Value *C, *D;
2992 if (match(LHS, m_SMax(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2993 match(RHS, m_SMin(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))) &&
2994 (A == C || A == D || B == C || B == D)) {
2995 // max(x, ?) pred min(x, ?).
2996 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
2997 // Always true.
2998 return getTrue(ITy);
2999 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
3000 // Always false.
3001 return getFalse(ITy);
3002 } else if (match(LHS, m_SMin(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
3003 match(RHS, m_SMax(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))) &&
3004 (A == C || A == D || B == C || B == D)) {
3005 // min(x, ?) pred max(x, ?).
3006 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
3007 // Always true.
3008 return getTrue(ITy);
3009 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
3010 // Always false.
3011 return getFalse(ITy);
3012 } else if (match(LHS, m_UMax(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
3013 match(RHS, m_UMin(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))) &&
3014 (A == C || A == D || B == C || B == D)) {
3015 // max(x, ?) pred min(x, ?).
3016 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
3017 // Always true.
3018 return getTrue(ITy);
3019 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
3020 // Always false.
3021 return getFalse(ITy);
3022 } else if (match(LHS, m_UMin(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
3023 match(RHS, m_UMax(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))) &&
3024 (A == C || A == D || B == C || B == D)) {
3025 // min(x, ?) pred max(x, ?).
3026 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
3027 // Always true.
3028 return getTrue(ITy);
3029 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
3030 // Always false.
3031 return getFalse(ITy);
3032 }
3033
3034 return nullptr;
3035}
3036
3037/// Given operands for an ICmpInst, see if we can fold the result.
3038/// If not, this returns null.
3039static Value *SimplifyICmpInst(unsigned Predicate, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
3040 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
3041 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = (CmpInst::Predicate)Predicate;
3042 assert(CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred) && "Not an integer compare!");
3043
3044 if (Constant *CLHS = dyn_cast<Constant>(LHS)) {
3045 if (Constant *CRHS = dyn_cast<Constant>(RHS))
3046 return ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Pred, CLHS, CRHS, Q.DL, Q.TLI);
3047
3048 // If we have a constant, make sure it is on the RHS.
3049 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
3050 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
3051 }
3052 assert(!isa<UndefValue>(LHS) && "Unexpected icmp undef,%X");
3053
3054 Type *ITy = GetCompareTy(LHS); // The return type.
3055
3056 // For EQ and NE, we can always pick a value for the undef to make the
3057 // predicate pass or fail, so we can return undef.
3058 // Matches behavior in llvm::ConstantFoldCompareInstruction.
3059 if (isa<UndefValue>(RHS) && ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred))
3060 return UndefValue::get(ITy);
3061
3062 // icmp X, X -> true/false
3063 // icmp X, undef -> true/false because undef could be X.
3064 if (LHS == RHS || isa<UndefValue>(RHS))
3065 return ConstantInt::get(ITy, CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred));
3066
3067 if (Value *V = simplifyICmpOfBools(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q))
3068 return V;
3069
3070 if (Value *V = simplifyICmpWithZero(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q))
3071 return V;
3072
3073 if (Value *V = simplifyICmpWithConstant(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q.IIQ))
3074 return V;
3075
3076 // If both operands have range metadata, use the metadata
3077 // to simplify the comparison.
3078 if (isa<Instruction>(RHS) && isa<Instruction>(LHS)) {
3079 auto RHS_Instr = cast<Instruction>(RHS);
3080 auto LHS_Instr = cast<Instruction>(LHS);
3081
3082 if (Q.IIQ.getMetadata(RHS_Instr, LLVMContext::MD_range) &&
3083 Q.IIQ.getMetadata(LHS_Instr, LLVMContext::MD_range)) {
3084 auto RHS_CR = getConstantRangeFromMetadata(
3085 *RHS_Instr->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range));
3086 auto LHS_CR = getConstantRangeFromMetadata(
3087 *LHS_Instr->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range));
3088
3089 auto Satisfied_CR = ConstantRange::makeSatisfyingICmpRegion(Pred, RHS_CR);
3090 if (Satisfied_CR.contains(LHS_CR))
3091 return ConstantInt::getTrue(RHS->getContext());
3092
3093 auto InversedSatisfied_CR = ConstantRange::makeSatisfyingICmpRegion(
3094 CmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred), RHS_CR);
3095 if (InversedSatisfied_CR.contains(LHS_CR))
3096 return ConstantInt::getFalse(RHS->getContext());
3097 }
3098 }
3099
3100 // Compare of cast, for example (zext X) != 0 -> X != 0
3101 if (isa<CastInst>(LHS) && (isa<Constant>(RHS) || isa<CastInst>(RHS))) {
3102 Instruction *LI = cast<CastInst>(LHS);
3103 Value *SrcOp = LI->getOperand(0);
3104 Type *SrcTy = SrcOp->getType();
3105 Type *DstTy = LI->getType();
3106
3107 // Turn icmp (ptrtoint x), (ptrtoint/constant) into a compare of the input
3108 // if the integer type is the same size as the pointer type.
3109 if (MaxRecurse && isa<PtrToIntInst>(LI) &&
3110 Q.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(SrcTy) == DstTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits()) {
3111 if (Constant *RHSC = dyn_cast<Constant>(RHS)) {
3112 // Transfer the cast to the constant.
3113 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, SrcOp,
3114 ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(RHSC, SrcTy),
3115 Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3116 return V;
3117 } else if (PtrToIntInst *RI = dyn_cast<PtrToIntInst>(RHS)) {
3118 if (RI->getOperand(0)->getType() == SrcTy)
3119 // Compare without the cast.
3120 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, SrcOp, RI->getOperand(0),
3121 Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3122 return V;
3123 }
3124 }
3125
3126 if (isa<ZExtInst>(LHS)) {
3127 // Turn icmp (zext X), (zext Y) into a compare of X and Y if they have the
3128 // same type.
3129 if (ZExtInst *RI = dyn_cast<ZExtInst>(RHS)) {
3130 if (MaxRecurse && SrcTy == RI->getOperand(0)->getType())
3131 // Compare X and Y. Note that signed predicates become unsigned.
3132 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(ICmpInst::getUnsignedPredicate(Pred),
3133 SrcOp, RI->getOperand(0), Q,
3134 MaxRecurse-1))
3135 return V;
3136 }
3137 // Turn icmp (zext X), Cst into a compare of X and Cst if Cst is extended
3138 // too. If not, then try to deduce the result of the comparison.
3139 else if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
3140 // Compute the constant that would happen if we truncated to SrcTy then
3141 // reextended to DstTy.
3142 Constant *Trunc = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(CI, SrcTy);
3143 Constant *RExt = ConstantExpr::getCast(CastInst::ZExt, Trunc, DstTy);
3144
3145 // If the re-extended constant didn't change then this is effectively
3146 // also a case of comparing two zero-extended values.
3147 if (RExt == CI && MaxRecurse)
3148 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(ICmpInst::getUnsignedPredicate(Pred),
3149 SrcOp, Trunc, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3150 return V;
3151
3152 // Otherwise the upper bits of LHS are zero while RHS has a non-zero bit
3153 // there. Use this to work out the result of the comparison.
3154 if (RExt != CI) {
3155 switch (Pred) {
3156 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown ICmp predicate!");
3157 // LHS <u RHS.
3158 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
3159 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
3160 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
3161 return ConstantInt::getFalse(CI->getContext());
3162
3163 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
3164 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
3165 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
3166 return ConstantInt::getTrue(CI->getContext());
3167
3168 // LHS is non-negative. If RHS is negative then LHS >s LHS. If RHS
3169 // is non-negative then LHS <s RHS.
3170 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
3171 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
3172 return CI->getValue().isNegative() ?
3173 ConstantInt::getTrue(CI->getContext()) :
3174 ConstantInt::getFalse(CI->getContext());
3175
3176 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
3177 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
3178 return CI->getValue().isNegative() ?
3179 ConstantInt::getFalse(CI->getContext()) :
3180 ConstantInt::getTrue(CI->getContext());
3181 }
3182 }
3183 }
3184 }
3185
3186 if (isa<SExtInst>(LHS)) {
3187 // Turn icmp (sext X), (sext Y) into a compare of X and Y if they have the
3188 // same type.
3189 if (SExtInst *RI = dyn_cast<SExtInst>(RHS)) {
3190 if (MaxRecurse && SrcTy == RI->getOperand(0)->getType())
3191 // Compare X and Y. Note that the predicate does not change.
3192 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, SrcOp, RI->getOperand(0),
3193 Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3194 return V;
3195 }
3196 // Turn icmp (sext X), Cst into a compare of X and Cst if Cst is extended
3197 // too. If not, then try to deduce the result of the comparison.
3198 else if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
3199 // Compute the constant that would happen if we truncated to SrcTy then
3200 // reextended to DstTy.
3201 Constant *Trunc = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(CI, SrcTy);
3202 Constant *RExt = ConstantExpr::getCast(CastInst::SExt, Trunc, DstTy);
3203
3204 // If the re-extended constant didn't change then this is effectively
3205 // also a case of comparing two sign-extended values.
3206 if (RExt == CI && MaxRecurse)
3207 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(Pred, SrcOp, Trunc, Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3208 return V;
3209
3210 // Otherwise the upper bits of LHS are all equal, while RHS has varying
3211 // bits there. Use this to work out the result of the comparison.
3212 if (RExt != CI) {
3213 switch (Pred) {
3214 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown ICmp predicate!");
3215 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
3216 return ConstantInt::getFalse(CI->getContext());
3217 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
3218 return ConstantInt::getTrue(CI->getContext());
3219
3220 // If RHS is non-negative then LHS <s RHS. If RHS is negative then
3221 // LHS >s RHS.
3222 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
3223 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
3224 return CI->getValue().isNegative() ?
3225 ConstantInt::getTrue(CI->getContext()) :
3226 ConstantInt::getFalse(CI->getContext());
3227 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
3228 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
3229 return CI->getValue().isNegative() ?
3230 ConstantInt::getFalse(CI->getContext()) :
3231 ConstantInt::getTrue(CI->getContext());
3232
3233 // If LHS is non-negative then LHS <u RHS. If LHS is negative then
3234 // LHS >u RHS.
3235 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
3236 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
3237 // Comparison is true iff the LHS <s 0.
3238 if (MaxRecurse)
3239 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, SrcOp,
3240 Constant::getNullValue(SrcTy),
3241 Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3242 return V;
3243 break;
3244 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
3245 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
3246 // Comparison is true iff the LHS >=s 0.
3247 if (MaxRecurse)
3248 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, SrcOp,
3249 Constant::getNullValue(SrcTy),
3250 Q, MaxRecurse-1))
3251 return V;
3252 break;
3253 }
3254 }
3255 }
3256 }
3257 }
3258
3259 // icmp eq|ne X, Y -> false|true if X != Y
3260 if (ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) &&
3261 isKnownNonEqual(LHS, RHS, Q.DL, Q.AC, Q.CxtI, Q.DT, Q.IIQ.UseInstrInfo)) {
3262 return Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE ? getTrue(ITy) : getFalse(ITy);
3263 }
3264
3265 if (Value *V = simplifyICmpWithBinOp(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse))
3266 return V;
3267
3268 if (Value *V = simplifyICmpWithMinMax(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse))
3269 return V;
3270
3271 // Simplify comparisons of related pointers using a powerful, recursive
3272 // GEP-walk when we have target data available..
3273 if (LHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
3274 if (auto *C = computePointerICmp(Q.DL, Q.TLI, Q.DT, Pred, Q.AC, Q.CxtI,
3275 Q.IIQ, LHS, RHS))
3276 return C;
3277 if (auto *CLHS = dyn_cast<PtrToIntOperator>(LHS))
3278 if (auto *CRHS = dyn_cast<PtrToIntOperator>(RHS))
3279 if (Q.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CLHS->getPointerOperandType()) ==
3280 Q.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CLHS->getType()) &&
3281 Q.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CRHS->getPointerOperandType()) ==
3282 Q.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CRHS->getType()))
3283 if (auto *C = computePointerICmp(Q.DL, Q.TLI, Q.DT, Pred, Q.AC, Q.CxtI,
3284 Q.IIQ, CLHS->getPointerOperand(),
3285 CRHS->getPointerOperand()))
3286 return C;
3287
3288 if (GetElementPtrInst *GLHS = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(LHS)) {
3289 if (GEPOperator *GRHS = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(RHS)) {
3290 if (GLHS->getPointerOperand() == GRHS->getPointerOperand() &&
3291 GLHS->hasAllConstantIndices() && GRHS->hasAllConstantIndices() &&
3292 (ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) ||
3293 (GLHS->isInBounds() && GRHS->isInBounds() &&
3294 Pred == ICmpInst::getSignedPredicate(Pred)))) {
3295 // The bases are equal and the indices are constant. Build a constant
3296 // expression GEP with the same indices and a null base pointer to see
3297 // what constant folding can make out of it.
3298 Constant *Null = Constant::getNullValue(GLHS->getPointerOperandType());
3299 SmallVector<Value *, 4> IndicesLHS(GLHS->idx_begin(), GLHS->idx_end());
3300 Constant *NewLHS = ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(
3301 GLHS->getSourceElementType(), Null, IndicesLHS);
3302
3303 SmallVector<Value *, 4> IndicesRHS(GRHS->idx_begin(), GRHS->idx_end());
3304 Constant *NewRHS = ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(
3305 GLHS->getSourceElementType(), Null, IndicesRHS);
3306 return ConstantExpr::getICmp(Pred, NewLHS, NewRHS);
3307 }
3308 }
3309 }
3310
3311 // If the comparison is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
3312 // comparing with either branch of the select always yields the same value.
3313 if (isa<SelectInst>(LHS) || isa<SelectInst>(RHS))
3314 if (Value *V = ThreadCmpOverSelect(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse))
3315 return V;
3316
3317 // If the comparison is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
3318 // doing the compare with each incoming phi value yields a common result.
3319 if (isa<PHINode>(LHS) || isa<PHINode>(RHS))
3320 if (Value *V = ThreadCmpOverPHI(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse))
3321 return V;
3322
3323 return nullptr;
3324}
3325
3326Value *llvm::SimplifyICmpInst(unsigned Predicate, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
3327 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
3328 return ::SimplifyICmpInst(Predicate, LHS, RHS, Q, RecursionLimit);
3329}

3331/// Given operands for an FCmpInst, see if we can fold the result.
3332/// If not, this returns null.
3333static Value *SimplifyFCmpInst(unsigned Predicate, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
3334 FastMathFlags FMF, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
3335 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
3336 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = (CmpInst::Predicate)Predicate;
3337 assert(CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred) && "Not an FP compare!");
3338
3339 if (Constant *CLHS = dyn_cast<Constant>(LHS)) {
3340 if (Constant *CRHS = dyn_cast<Constant>(RHS))
3341 return ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Pred, CLHS, CRHS, Q.DL, Q.TLI);
3342
3343 // If we have a constant, make sure it is on the RHS.
3344 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
3345 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
3346 }
3347
3348 // Fold trivial predicates.
3349 Type *RetTy = GetCompareTy(LHS);
3350 if (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_FALSE)
3351 return getFalse(RetTy);
3352 if (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_TRUE)
3353 return getTrue(RetTy);
3354
3355 // Fold (un)ordered comparison if we can determine there are no NaNs.
3356 if (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD)
3357 if (FMF.noNaNs() ||
3358 (isKnownNeverNaN(LHS, Q.TLI) && isKnownNeverNaN(RHS, Q.TLI)))
3359 return ConstantInt::get(RetTy, Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD);
3360
3361 // NaN is unordered; NaN is not ordered.
3362 assert((FCmpInst::isOrdered(Pred) || FCmpInst::isUnordered(Pred)) &&
3363 "Comparison must be either ordered or unordered");
3364 if (match(RHS, m_NaN()))
3365 return ConstantInt::get(RetTy, CmpInst::isUnordered(Pred));
3366
3367 // fcmp pred x, undef and fcmp pred undef, x
3368 // fold to true if unordered, false if ordered
3369 if (isa<UndefValue>(LHS) || isa<UndefValue>(RHS)) {
3370 // Choosing NaN for the undef will always make unordered comparison succeed
3371 // and ordered comparison fail.
3372 return ConstantInt::get(RetTy, CmpInst::isUnordered(Pred));
3373 }
3374
3375 // fcmp x,x -> true/false. Not all compares are foldable.
3376 if (LHS == RHS) {
3377 if (CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred))
3378 return getTrue(RetTy);
3379 if (CmpInst::isFalseWhenEqual(Pred))
3380 return getFalse(RetTy);
3381 }
3382
3383 // Handle fcmp with constant RHS.
3384 // TODO: Use match with a specific FP value, so these work with vectors with
3385 // undef lanes.
3386 const APFloat *C;
3387 if (match(RHS, m_APFloat(C))) {
3388 // Check whether the constant is an infinity.
3389 if (C->isInfinity()) {
3390 if (C->isNegative()) {
3391 switch (Pred) {
3392 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
3393 // No value is ordered and less than negative infinity.
3394 return getFalse(RetTy);
3395 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
3396 // All values are unordered with or at least negative infinity.
3397 return getTrue(RetTy);
3398 default:
3399 break;
3400 }
3401 } else {
3402 switch (Pred) {
3403 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
3404 // No value is ordered and greater than infinity.
3405 return getFalse(RetTy);
3406 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
3407 // All values are unordered with and at most infinity.
3408 return getTrue(RetTy);
3409 default:
3410 break;
3411 }
3412 }
3413 }
3414 if (C->isNegative() && !C->isNegZero()) {
3415 assert(!C->isNaN() && "Unexpected NaN constant!");
3416 // TODO: We can catch more cases by using a range check rather than
3417 // relying on CannotBeOrderedLessThanZero.
3418 switch (Pred) {
3419 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
3420 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
3421 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE:
3422 // (X >= 0) implies (X > C) when (C < 0)
3423 if (CannotBeOrderedLessThanZero(LHS, Q.TLI))
3424 return getTrue(RetTy);
3425 break;
3426 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ:
3427 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
3428 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
3429 // (X >= 0) implies !(X < C) when (C < 0)
3430 if (CannotBeOrderedLessThanZero(LHS, Q.TLI))
3431 return getFalse(RetTy);
3432 break;
3433 default:
3434 break;
3435 }
3436 }
3437
3438 // Check comparison of [minnum/maxnum with constant] with other constant.
3439 const APFloat *C2;
3440 if ((match(LHS, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::minnum>(m_Value(), m_APFloat(C2))) &&
3441 C2->compare(*C) == APFloat::cmpLessThan) ||
3442 (match(LHS, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::maxnum>(m_Value(), m_APFloat(C2))) &&
3443 C2->compare(*C) == APFloat::cmpGreaterThan)) {
3444 bool IsMaxNum =
3445 cast<IntrinsicInst>(LHS)->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::maxnum;
3446 // The ordered relationship and minnum/maxnum guarantee that we do not
3447 // have NaN constants, so ordered/unordered preds are handled the same.
3448 switch (Pred) {
3449 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ: case FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ:
3450 // minnum(X, LesserC) == C --> false
3451 // maxnum(X, GreaterC) == C --> false
3452 return getFalse(RetTy);
3453 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE: case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE:
3454 // minnum(X, LesserC) != C --> true
3455 // maxnum(X, GreaterC) != C --> true
3456 return getTrue(RetTy);
3457 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
3458 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT: case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
3459 // minnum(X, LesserC) >= C --> false
3460 // minnum(X, LesserC) > C --> false
3461 // maxnum(X, GreaterC) >= C --> true
3462 // maxnum(X, GreaterC) > C --> true
3463 return ConstantInt::get(RetTy, IsMaxNum);
3464 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
3465 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT: case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
3466 // minnum(X, LesserC) <= C --> true
3467 // minnum(X, LesserC) < C --> true
3468 // maxnum(X, GreaterC) <= C --> false
3469 // maxnum(X, GreaterC) < C --> false
3470 return ConstantInt::get(RetTy, !IsMaxNum);
3471 default:
3472 // TRUE/FALSE/ORD/UNO should be handled before this.
3473 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected fcmp predicate");
3474 }
3475 }
3476 }
3477
3478 if (match(RHS, m_AnyZeroFP())) {
3479 switch (Pred) {
3480 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
3481 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
3482 // Positive or zero X >= 0.0 --> true
3483 // Positive or zero X < 0.0 --> false
3484 if ((FMF.noNaNs() || isKnownNeverNaN(LHS, Q.TLI)) &&
3485 CannotBeOrderedLessThanZero(LHS, Q.TLI))
3486 return Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE ? getTrue(RetTy) : getFalse(RetTy);
3487 break;
3488 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
3489 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
3490 // Positive or zero or nan X >= 0.0 --> true
3491 // Positive or zero or nan X < 0.0 --> false
3492 if (CannotBeOrderedLessThanZero(LHS, Q.TLI))
3493 return Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE ? getTrue(RetTy) : getFalse(RetTy);
3494 break;
3495 default:
3496 break;
3497 }
3498 }
3499
3500 // If the comparison is with the result of a select instruction, check whether
3501 // comparing with either branch of the select always yields the same value.
3502 if (isa<SelectInst>(LHS) || isa<SelectInst>(RHS))
3503 if (Value *V = ThreadCmpOverSelect(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse))
3504 return V;
3505
3506 // If the comparison is with the result of a phi instruction, check whether
3507 // doing the compare with each incoming phi value yields a common result.
3508 if (isa<PHINode>(LHS) || isa<PHINode>(RHS))
3509 if (Value *V = ThreadCmpOverPHI(Pred, LHS, RHS, Q, MaxRecurse))
3510 return V;
3511
3512 return nullptr;
3513}

3515Value *llvm::SimplifyFCmpInst(unsigned Predicate, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
3516 FastMathFlags FMF, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
3517 return ::SimplifyFCmpInst(Predicate, LHS, RHS, FMF, Q, RecursionLimit);
3518}

3520/// See if V simplifies when its operand Op is replaced with RepOp.
3521static const Value *SimplifyWithOpReplaced(Value *V, Value *Op, Value *RepOp,
3522 const SimplifyQuery &Q,
3523 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
3524 // Trivial replacement.
3525 if (V == Op)
3526 return RepOp;
3527
3528 // We cannot replace a constant, and shouldn't even try.
3529 if (isa<Constant>(Op))
3530 return nullptr;
3531
3532 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
3533 if (!I)
3534 return nullptr;
3535
3536 // If this is a binary operator, try to simplify it with the replaced op.
3537 if (auto *B = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(I)) {
3538 // Consider:
3539 // %cmp = icmp eq i32 %x, 2147483647
3540 // %add = add nsw i32 %x, 1
3541 // %sel = select i1 %cmp, i32 -2147483648, i32 %add
3542 //
3543 // We can't replace %sel with %add unless we strip away the flags.
3544 if (isa<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(B))
3545 if (Q.IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(B) || Q.IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(B))
3546 return nullptr;
3547 if (isa<PossiblyExactOperator>(B) && Q.IIQ.isExact(B))
3548 return nullptr;
3549
3550 if (MaxRecurse) {
3551 if (B->getOperand(0) == Op)
3552 return SimplifyBinOp(B->getOpcode(), RepOp, B->getOperand(1), Q,
3553 MaxRecurse - 1);
3554 if (B->getOperand(1) == Op)
3555 return SimplifyBinOp(B->getOpcode(), B->getOperand(0), RepOp, Q,
3556 MaxRecurse - 1);
3557 }
3558 }
3559
3560 // Same for CmpInsts.
3561 if (CmpInst *C = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(I)) {
3562 if (MaxRecurse) {
3563 if (C->getOperand(0) == Op)
3564 return SimplifyCmpInst(C->getPredicate(), RepOp, C->getOperand(1), Q,
3565 MaxRecurse - 1);
3566 if (C->getOperand(1) == Op)
3567 return SimplifyCmpInst(C->getPredicate(), C->getOperand(0), RepOp, Q,
3568 MaxRecurse - 1);
3569 }
3570 }
3571
3572 // Same for GEPs.
3573 if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(I)) {
3574 if (MaxRecurse) {
3575 SmallVector<Value *, 8> NewOps(GEP->getNumOperands());
3576 transform(GEP->operands(), NewOps.begin(),
3577 [&](Value *V) { return V == Op ? RepOp : V; });
3578 return SimplifyGEPInst(GEP->getSourceElementType(), NewOps, Q,
3579 MaxRecurse - 1);
3580 }
3581 }
3582
3583 // TODO: We could hand off more cases to instsimplify here.
3584
3585 // If all operands are constant after substituting Op for RepOp then we can
3586 // constant fold the instruction.
3587 if (Constant *CRepOp = dyn_cast<Constant>(RepOp)) {
3588 // Build a list of all constant operands.
3589 SmallVector<Constant *, 8> ConstOps;
3590 for (unsigned i = 0, e = I->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
3591 if (I->getOperand(i) == Op)
3592 ConstOps.push_back(CRepOp);
3593 else if (Constant *COp = dyn_cast<Constant>(I->getOperand(i)))
3594 ConstOps.push_back(COp);
3595 else
3596 break;
3597 }
3598
3599 // All operands were constants, fold it.
3600 if (ConstOps.size() == I->getNumOperands()) {
3601 if (CmpInst *C = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(I))
3602 return ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(C->getPredicate(), ConstOps[0],
3603 ConstOps[1], Q.DL, Q.TLI);
3604
3605 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(I))
3606 if (!LI->isVolatile())
3607 return ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(ConstOps[0], LI->getType(), Q.DL);
3608
3609 return ConstantFoldInstOperands(I, ConstOps, Q.DL, Q.TLI);
3610 }
3611 }
3612
3613 return nullptr;
3614}
3615
3616/// Try to simplify a select instruction when its condition operand is an
3617/// integer comparison where one operand of the compare is a constant.
3618static Value *simplifySelectBitTest(Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal, Value *X,
3619 const APInt *Y, bool TrueWhenUnset) {
3620 const APInt *C;
3621
3622 // (X & Y) == 0 ? X & ~Y : X --> X
3623 // (X & Y) != 0 ? X & ~Y : X --> X & ~Y
3624 if (FalseVal == X && match(TrueVal, m_And(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(C))) &&
3625 *Y == ~*C)
3626 return TrueWhenUnset ? FalseVal : TrueVal;
3627
3628 // (X & Y) == 0 ? X : X & ~Y --> X & ~Y
3629 // (X & Y) != 0 ? X : X & ~Y --> X
3630 if (TrueVal == X && match(FalseVal, m_And(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(C))) &&
3631 *Y == ~*C)
3632 return TrueWhenUnset ? FalseVal : TrueVal;
3633
3634 if (Y->isPowerOf2()) {
3635 // (X & Y) == 0 ? X | Y : X --> X | Y
3636 // (X & Y) != 0 ? X | Y : X --> X
3637 if (FalseVal == X && match(TrueVal, m_Or(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(C))) &&
3638 *Y == *C)
3639 return TrueWhenUnset ? TrueVal : FalseVal;
3640
3641 // (X & Y) == 0 ? X : X | Y --> X
3642 // (X & Y) != 0 ? X : X | Y --> X | Y
3643 if (TrueVal == X && match(FalseVal, m_Or(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(C))) &&
3644 *Y == *C)
3645 return TrueWhenUnset ? TrueVal : FalseVal;
3646 }
3647
3648 return nullptr;
3649}
3650
3651/// An alternative way to test if a bit is set or not uses sgt/slt instead of
3652/// eq/ne.
3653static Value *simplifySelectWithFakeICmpEq(Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
3654 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred,
3655 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal) {
3656 Value *X;
3657 APInt Mask;
3658 if (!decomposeBitTestICmp(CmpLHS, CmpRHS, Pred, X, Mask))
3659 return nullptr;
3660
3661 return simplifySelectBitTest(TrueVal, FalseVal, X, &Mask,
3662 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ);
3663}
3664
3665/// Try to simplify a select instruction when its condition operand is an
3666/// integer comparison.
3667static Value *simplifySelectWithICmpCond(Value *CondVal, Value *TrueVal,
3668 Value *FalseVal, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
3669 unsigned MaxRecurse) {
3670 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
3671 Value *CmpLHS, *CmpRHS;
3672 if (!match(CondVal, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Value(CmpLHS), m_Value(CmpRHS))))
3673 return nullptr;
3674
3675 if (ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) && match(CmpRHS, m_Zero())) {
3676 Value *X;
3677 const APInt *Y;
3678 if (match(CmpLHS, m_And(m_Value(X), m_APInt(Y))))
3679 if (Value *V = simplifySelectBitTest(TrueVal, FalseVal, X, Y,
3680 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ))
3681 return V;
3682
3683 // Test for a bogus zero-shift-guard-op around funnel-shift or rotate.
3684 Value *ShAmt;
3685 auto isFsh = m_CombineOr(m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::fshl>(m_Value(X), m_Value(),
3686 m_Value(ShAmt)),
3687 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::fshr>(m_Value(), m_Value(X),
3688 m_Value(ShAmt)));
3689 // (ShAmt == 0) ? fshl(X, *, ShAmt) : X --> X
3690 // (ShAmt == 0) ? fshr(*, X, ShAmt) : X --> X
3691 if (match(TrueVal, isFsh) && FalseVal == X && CmpLHS == ShAmt &&
3692 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
3693 return X;
3694 // (ShAmt != 0) ? X : fshl(X, *, ShAmt) --> X
3695 // (ShAmt != 0) ? X : fshr(*, X, ShAmt) --> X
3696 if (match(FalseVal, isFsh) && TrueVal == X && CmpLHS == ShAmt &&
3697 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
3698 return X;
3699
3700 // Test for a zero-shift-guard-op around rotates. These are used to
3701 // avoid UB from oversized shifts in raw IR rotate patterns, but the
3702 // intrinsics do not have that problem.
3703 // We do not allow this transform for the general funnel shift case because
3704 // that would not preserve the poison safety of the original code.
3705 auto isRotate = m_CombineOr(m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::fshl>(m_Value(X),
3706 m_Deferred(X),
3707 m_Value(ShAmt)),
3708 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::fshr>(m_Value(X),
3709 m_Deferred(X),
3710 m_Value(ShAmt)));
3711 // (ShAmt != 0) ? fshl(X, X, ShAmt) : X --> fshl(X, X, ShAmt)
3712 // (ShAmt != 0) ? fshr(X, X, ShAmt) : X --> fshr(X, X, ShAmt)
3713 if (match(TrueVal, isRotate) && FalseVal == X && CmpLHS == ShAmt &&
3714 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
3715 return TrueVal;
3716 // (ShAmt == 0) ? X : fshl(X, X, ShAmt) --> fshl(X, X, ShAmt)
3717 // (ShAmt == 0) ? X : fshr(X, X, ShAmt) --> fshr(X, X, ShAmt)
3718 if (match(FalseVal, isRotate) && TrueVal == X && CmpLHS == ShAmt &&
3719 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
3720 return FalseVal;
3721 }
3722
3723 // Check for other compares that behave like bit test.
3724 if (Value *V = simplifySelectWithFakeICmpEq(CmpLHS, CmpRHS, Pred,
3725 TrueVal, FalseVal))
3726 return V;
3727
3728 // If we have an equality comparison, then we know the value in one of the
3729 // arms of the select. See if substituting this value into the arm and
3730 // simplifying the result yields the same value as the other arm.
3731 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ) {
3732 if (SimplifyWithOpReplaced(FalseVal, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3733 TrueVal ||
3734 SimplifyWithOpReplaced(FalseVal, CmpRHS, CmpLHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3735 TrueVal)
3736 return FalseVal;
3737 if (SimplifyWithOpReplaced(TrueVal, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3738 FalseVal ||
3739 SimplifyWithOpReplaced(TrueVal, CmpRHS, CmpLHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3740 FalseVal)
3741 return FalseVal;
3742 } else if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE) {
3743 if (SimplifyWithOpReplaced(TrueVal, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3744 FalseVal ||
3745 SimplifyWithOpReplaced(TrueVal, CmpRHS, CmpLHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3746 FalseVal)
3747 return TrueVal;
3748 if (SimplifyWithOpReplaced(FalseVal, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3749 TrueVal ||
3750 SimplifyWithOpReplaced(FalseVal, CmpRHS, CmpLHS, Q, MaxRecurse) ==
3751 TrueVal)
3752 return TrueVal;
3753 }
3754
3755 return nullptr;
3756}
3757
3758/// Try to simplify a select instruction when its condition operand is a
3759/// floating-point comparison.
3760static Value *simplifySelectWithFCmp(Value *Cond, Value *T, Value *F) {
3761 FCmpInst::Predicate Pred;
3762 if (!match(Cond, m_FCmp(Pred, m_Specific(T), m_Specific(F))) &&
3763 !match(Cond, m_FCmp(Pred, m_Specific(F), m_Specific(T))))
3764 return nullptr;
3765
3766 // TODO: The transform may not be valid with -0.0. An incomplete way of
3767 // testing for that possibility is to check if at least one operand is a
3768 // non-zero constant.
3769 const APFloat *C;
3770 if ((match(T, m_APFloat(C)) && C->isNonZero()) ||
3771 (match(F, m_APFloat(C)) && C->isNonZero())) {
3772 // (T == F) ? T : F --> F
3773 // (F == T) ? T : F --> F
3774 if (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ)
3775 return F;
3776
3777 // (T != F) ? T : F --> T
3778 // (F != T) ? T : F --> T
3779 if (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE)
3780 return T;
3781 }
3782
3783 return nullptr;
3784}

3786/// Given operands for a SelectInst, see if we can fold the result.
3787/// If not, this returns null.
3788static Value *SimplifySelectInst(Value *Cond, Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
3789 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
3790 if (auto *CondC = dyn_cast<Constant>(Cond)) {
3791 if (auto *TrueC = dyn_cast<Constant>(TrueVal))
3792 if (auto *FalseC = dyn_cast<Constant>(FalseVal))
3793 return ConstantFoldSelectInstruction(CondC, TrueC, FalseC);
3794
3795 // select undef, X, Y -> X or Y
3796 if (isa<UndefValue>(CondC))
3797 return isa<Constant>(FalseVal) ? FalseVal : TrueVal;
3798
3799 // TODO: Vector constants with undef elements don't simplify.
3800
3801 // select true, X, Y -> X
3802 if (CondC->isAllOnesValue())
3803 return TrueVal;
3804 // select false, X, Y -> Y
3805 if (CondC->isNullValue())
3806 return FalseVal;
3807 }
3808
3809 // select ?, X, X -> X
3810 if (TrueVal == FalseVal)
3811 return TrueVal;
3812
3813 if (isa<UndefValue>(TrueVal)) // select ?, undef, X -> X
3814 return FalseVal;
3815 if (isa<UndefValue>(FalseVal)) // select ?, X, undef -> X
3816 return TrueVal;
3817
3818 if (Value *V =
3819 simplifySelectWithICmpCond(Cond, TrueVal, FalseVal, Q, MaxRecurse))
3820 return V;
3821
3822 if (Value *V = simplifySelectWithFCmp(Cond, TrueVal, FalseVal))
3823 return V;
3824
3825 if (Value *V = foldSelectWithBinaryOp(Cond, TrueVal, FalseVal))
3826 return V;
3827
3828 Optional<bool> Imp = isImpliedByDomCondition(Cond, Q.CxtI, Q.DL);
3829 if (Imp)
3830 return *Imp ? TrueVal : FalseVal;
3831
3832 return nullptr;
3833}

3836 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
3837 return ::SimplifySelectInst(Cond, TrueVal, FalseVal, Q, RecursionLimit);
3838}

3840/// Given operands for an GetElementPtrInst, see if we can fold the result.
3841/// If not, this returns null.
3842static Value *SimplifyGEPInst(Type *SrcTy, ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
3843 const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned) {
3844 // The type of the GEP pointer operand.
3845 unsigned AS =
3846 cast<PointerType>(Ops[0]->getType()->getScalarType())->getAddressSpace();
3847
3848 // getelementptr P -> P.
3849 if (Ops.size() == 1)
3850 return Ops[0];
3851
3852 // Compute the (pointer) type returned by the GEP instruction.
3853 Type *LastType = GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(SrcTy, Ops.slice(1));
3854 Type *GEPTy = PointerType::get(LastType, AS);
3855 if (VectorType *VT = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Ops[0]->getType()))
3856 GEPTy = VectorType::get(GEPTy, VT->getNumElements());
3857 else if (VectorType *VT = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Ops[1]->getType()))
3858 GEPTy = VectorType::get(GEPTy, VT->getNumElements());
3859
3860 if (isa<UndefValue>(Ops[0]))
3861 return UndefValue::get(GEPTy);
3862
3863 if (Ops.size() == 2) {
3864 // getelementptr P, 0 -> P.
3865 if (match(Ops[1], m_Zero()) && Ops[0]->getType() == GEPTy)
3866 return Ops[0];
3867
3868 Type *Ty = SrcTy;
3869 if (Ty->isSized()) {
3870 Value *P;
3871 uint64_t C;
3872 uint64_t TyAllocSize = Q.DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty);
3873 // getelementptr P, N -> P if P points to a type of zero size.
3874 if (TyAllocSize == 0 && Ops[0]->getType() == GEPTy)
3875 return Ops[0];
3876
3877 // The following transforms are only safe if the ptrtoint cast
3878 // doesn't truncate the pointers.
3879 if (Ops[1]->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() ==
3880 Q.DL.getIndexSizeInBits(AS)) {
3881 auto PtrToIntOrZero = [GEPTy](Value *P) -> Value * {
3882 if (match(P, m_Zero()))
3883 return Constant::getNullValue(GEPTy);
3884 Value *Temp;
3885 if (match(P, m_PtrToInt(m_Value(Temp))))
3886 if (Temp->getType() == GEPTy)
3887 return Temp;
3888 return nullptr;
3889 };
3890
3891 // getelementptr V, (sub P, V) -> P if P points to a type of size 1.
3892 if (TyAllocSize == 1 &&
3893 match(Ops[1], m_Sub(m_Value(P), m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(Ops[0])))))
3894 if (Value *R = PtrToIntOrZero(P))
3895 return R;
3896
3897 // getelementptr V, (ashr (sub P, V), C) -> Q
3898 // if P points to a type of size 1 << C.
3899 if (match(Ops[1],
3900 m_AShr(m_Sub(m_Value(P), m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(Ops[0]))),
3901 m_ConstantInt(C))) &&
3902 TyAllocSize == 1ULL << C)
3903 if (Value *R = PtrToIntOrZero(P))
3904 return R;
3905
3906 // getelementptr V, (sdiv (sub P, V), C) -> Q
3907 // if P points to a type of size C.
3908 if (match(Ops[1],
3909 m_SDiv(m_Sub(m_Value(P), m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(Ops[0]))),
3910 m_SpecificInt(TyAllocSize))))
3911 if (Value *R = PtrToIntOrZero(P))
3912 return R;
3913 }
3914 }
3915 }
3916
3917 if (Q.DL.getTypeAllocSize(LastType) == 1 &&
3918 all_of(Ops.slice(1).drop_back(1),
3919 [](Value *Idx) { return match(Idx, m_Zero()); })) {
3920 unsigned IdxWidth =
3921 Q.DL.getIndexSizeInBits(Ops[0]->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
3922 if (Q.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(Ops.back()->getType()) == IdxWidth) {
3923 APInt BasePtrOffset(IdxWidth, 0);
3924 Value *StrippedBasePtr =
3925 Ops[0]->stripAndAccumulateInBoundsConstantOffsets(Q.DL,
3926 BasePtrOffset);
3927
3928 // gep (gep V, C), (sub 0, V) -> C
3929 if (match(Ops.back(),
3930 m_Sub(m_Zero(), m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(StrippedBasePtr))))) {
3931 auto *CI = ConstantInt::get(GEPTy->getContext(), BasePtrOffset);
3932 return ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(CI, GEPTy);
3933 }
3934 // gep (gep V, C), (xor V, -1) -> C-1
3935 if (match(Ops.back(),
3936 m_Xor(m_PtrToInt(m_Specific(StrippedBasePtr)), m_AllOnes()))) {
3937 auto *CI = ConstantInt::get(GEPTy->getContext(), BasePtrOffset - 1);
3938 return ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(CI, GEPTy);
3939 }
3940 }
3941 }
3942
3943 // Check to see if this is constant foldable.
3944 if (!all_of(Ops, [](Value *V) { return isa<Constant>(V); }))
3945 return nullptr;
3946
3947 auto *CE = ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(SrcTy, cast<Constant>(Ops[0]),
3948 Ops.slice(1));
3949 if (auto *CEFolded = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, Q.DL))
3950 return CEFolded;
3951 return CE;
3952}

3956 return ::SimplifyGEPInst(SrcTy, Ops, Q, RecursionLimit);

3959/// Given operands for an InsertValueInst, see if we can fold the result.
3960/// If not, this returns null.
3961static Value *SimplifyInsertValueInst(Value *Agg, Value *Val,
3962 ArrayRef<unsigned> Idxs, const SimplifyQuery &Q,
3963 unsigned) {
3964 if (Constant *CAgg = dyn_cast<Constant>(Agg))
3965 if (Constant *CVal = dyn_cast<Constant>(Val))
3966 return ConstantFoldInsertValueInstruction(CAgg, CVal, Idxs);
3967
3968 // insertvalue x, undef, n -> x
3969 if (match(Val, m_Undef()))
3970 return Agg;
3971
3972 // insertvalue x, (extractvalue y, n), n
3973 if (ExtractValueInst *EV = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(Val))
3974 if (EV->getAggregateOperand()->getType() == Agg->getType() &&
3975 EV->getIndices() == Idxs) {
3976 // insertvalue undef, (extractvalue y, n), n -> y
3977 if (match(Agg, m_Undef()))
3978 return EV->getAggregateOperand();
3979
3980 // insertvalue y, (extractvalue y, n), n -> y
3981 if (Agg == EV->getAggregateOperand())
3982 return Agg;
3983 }
3984
3985 return nullptr;
3986}

3989 ArrayRef<unsigned> Idxs,
3990 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
3991 return ::SimplifyInsertValueInst(Agg, Val, Idxs, Q, RecursionLimit);
3992}

3994Value *llvm::SimplifyInsertElementInst(Value *Vec, Value *Val, Value *Idx,
3995 const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
3996 // Try to constant fold.
3997 auto *VecC = dyn_cast<Constant>(Vec);
3998 auto *ValC = dyn_cast<Constant>(Val);
3999 auto *IdxC = dyn_cast<Constant>(Idx);
4000 if (VecC && ValC && IdxC)
4001 return ConstantFoldInsertElementInstruction(VecC, ValC, IdxC);
4002
4003 // Fold into undef if index is out of bounds.
4004 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Idx)) {
4005 uint64_t NumElements = cast<VectorType>(Vec->getType())->getNumElements();
4006 if (CI->uge(NumElements))
4007 return UndefValue::get(Vec->getType());
4008 }
4009
4010 // If index is undef, it might be out of bounds (see above case)
4011 if (isa<UndefValue>(Idx))
4012 return UndefValue::get(Vec->getType());
4013
4014 // Inserting an undef scalar? Assume it is the same value as the existing
4015 // vector element.
4016 if (isa<UndefValue>(Val))
4017 return Vec;
4018
4019 // If we are extracting a value from a vector, then inserting it into the same
4020 // place, that's the input vector:
4021 // insertelt Vec, (extractelt Vec, Idx), Idx --> Vec
4022 if (match(Val, m_ExtractElement(m_Specific(Vec), m_Specific(Idx))))
4023 return Vec;
4024
4025 return nullptr;
4026}

4028/// Given operands for an ExtractValueInst, see if we can fold the result.
4029/// If not, this returns null.
4030static Value *SimplifyExtractValueInst(Value *Agg, ArrayRef<unsigned> Idxs,
4031 const SimplifyQuery &, unsigned) {
4032 if (auto *CAgg = dyn_cast<Constant>(Agg))
4033 return ConstantFoldExtractValueInstruction(CAgg, Idxs);
4034
4035 // extractvalue x, (insertvalue y, elt, n), n -> elt
4036 unsigned NumIdxs = Idxs.size();
4037 for (auto *IVI = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(Agg); IVI != nullptr;
4038 IVI = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(IVI->getAggregateOperand())) {
4039 ArrayRef<unsigned> InsertValueIdxs = IVI->getIndices();
4040 unsigned NumInsertValueIdxs = InsertValueIdxs.size();
4041 unsigned NumCommonIdxs = std::min(NumInsertValueIdxs, NumIdxs);
4042 if (InsertValueIdxs.slice(0, NumCommonIdxs) ==
4043 Idxs.slice(0, NumCommonIdxs)) {
4044 if (NumIdxs == NumInsertValueIdxs)
4045 return IVI->getInsertedValueOperand();
4046 break;
4047 }
4048 }
4049
4050 return nullptr;
4051}

4058/// Given operands for an ExtractElementInst, see if we can fold the result.
4059/// If not, this returns null.
4060static Value *SimplifyExtractElementInst(Value *Vec, Value *Idx, const SimplifyQuery &,
4061 unsigned) {
4062 if (auto *CVec = dyn_cast<Constant>(Vec)) {
4063 if (auto *CIdx = dyn_cast<Constant>(Idx))
4064 return ConstantFoldExtractElementInstruction(CVec, CIdx);
4065
4066 // The index is not relevant if our vector is a splat.
4067 if (auto *Splat = CVec->getSplatValue())
4068 return Splat;
4069
4070 if (isa<UndefValue>(Vec))
4071 return UndefValue::get(Vec->getType()->getVectorElementType());
4072 }
4073
4074 // If extracting a specified index from the vector, see if we can recursively
4075 // find a previously computed scalar that was inserted into the vector.
4076 if (auto *IdxC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Idx)) {
4077 if (IdxC->getValue().uge(Vec->getType()->getVectorNumElements()))
4078 // definitely out of bounds, thus undefined result
4079 return UndefValue::get(Vec->getType()->getVectorElementType());
4080 if (Value *Elt = findScalarElement(Vec, IdxC->getZExtValue()))
4081 return Elt;
4082 }
4083
4084 // An undef extract index can be arbitrarily chosen to be an out-of-range
4085 // index value, which would result in the instruction being undef.
4086 if (isa<UndefValue>(Idx))
4087 return UndefValue::get(Vec->getType()->getVectorElementType());
4088
4089 return nullptr;
4090}

4097/// See if we can fold the given phi. If not, returns null.
4098static Value *SimplifyPHINode(PHINode *PN, const SimplifyQuery &Q) {
4099 // If all of the PHI's incoming values are the same then replace the PHI node
4100 // with the common value.
4101 Value *CommonValue = nullptr;
4102 bool HasUndefInput = false;
4103 for (Value *Incoming : PN->incoming_values()) {
4104 // If the incoming value is the phi node itself, it can safely be skipped.
4105 if (Incoming == PN) continue;
4106 if (isa<UndefValue>(Incoming)) {
4107 // Remember that we saw an undef value, but otherwise ignore them.
4108 HasUndefInput = true;
4109 continue;
4110 }
4111 if (CommonValue && Incoming != CommonValue)
4112 return nullptr; // Not the same, bail out.
4113 CommonValue = Incoming;
4114 }
4115
4116 // If CommonValue is null then all of the incoming values were either undef or
4117 // equal to the phi node itself.
4118 if (!CommonValue)
4119 return UndefValue::get(PN->getType());
4120
4121 // If we have a PHI node like phi(X, undef, X), where X is defined by some
4122 // instruction, we cannot return X as the result of the PHI node unless it
4123 // dominates the PHI block.
4124 if (HasUndefInput)
4125 return valueDominatesPHI(CommonValue, PN, Q.DT) ? CommonValue : nullptr;
4126
4127 return CommonValue;
4128}

4130static Value *SimplifyCastInst(unsigned CastOpc, Value *Op,
4131 Type *Ty, const SimplifyQuery &Q, unsigned MaxRecurse) {
4132 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op))
4133 return ConstantFoldCastOperand(CastOpc, C, Ty, Q.DL);
4134
4135 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(Op)) {
4136 auto *Src = CI->getOperand(0);
4137 Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
4138 Type *MidTy = CI->getType();
4139 Type *DstTy = Ty;
4140 if (Src->getType() == Ty) {
4141 auto FirstOp = static_cast<Instruction::CastOps>(CI->getOpcode());
4142 auto SecondOp = static_cast<Instruction::CastOps>(CastOpc);
4143 Type *SrcIntPtrTy =
4144 SrcTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() ? Q.DL.getIntPtrType(SrcTy) : nullptr;
4145 Type *MidIntPtrTy =
4146 MidTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() ? Q.DL.getIntPtrType(MidTy) : nullptr;
4147 Type *DstIntPtrTy =
4148 DstTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() ? Q.DL.getIntPtrType(DstTy) : nullptr;
4149 if (CastInst::isEliminableCastPair(FirstOp, SecondOp, SrcTy, MidTy, DstTy,
4150 SrcIntPtrTy, MidIntPtrTy,
4151 DstIntPtrTy) == Instruction::BitCast)
4152 return Src;
4153 }
4154 }
4155
4156 // bitcast x -> x
4157 if (CastOpc == Instruction::BitCast)
4158 if (Op->getType() == Ty)
4159 return Op;
4160
4161 return nullptr;
4162}

4166 return ::SimplifyCastInst(CastOpc, Op, Ty, Q, RecursionLimit);
